1307	bd8619cb-5508-473c-8fef-b860f0ce1b07	Is Our Generation Giving Up On Love? 5 Reasons it Might Be	is-our-generation-giving-up-on-love-5-reason-it-might-be	\n**By [Kate Rae](http://katerae.wordpress.com)**  \n**“Love, love, love…all you need is love.”– The Beatles**\n\nWhat will people say about our generation? ” Well, they took millions of ‘selfies’ and they put out music called ‘trap queen’…” . Wow, I really don’t ever want to be someone’s trap queen…I really don’t even understand what that is.\n\nAs I witness some of our generation slowly begin to wake up, it gives me hope that we could be remembered for something great. I believe in soulmates and that there are certain people meant for you, at a certain time along your life path. I think, when you are your best (or close to it), you meet your unique counterpart. Who wouldn’t want to experience that?\n\nThe more you focus on loving yourself and those around you who deserve it (and some who don’t), the more positive the vibes you are leaking out. I wish people would just realize how important love is, because love is powerful and it could save us from a world full of selfishness, hatred, and greed.\n\nHere are some reasons why I think people are giving up on love.\n\n- **Speed Dating. **This is basically what people do, trying to find their ‘one and only’ rapidly moving through people like there is no tomorrow. Where is the spontaneity in that? The romance? No where. Dating as a sport isn’t going to get you any closer to ‘the one’. Dating someone who isn’t right for you just for the sake of dating will lead you nowhere but straight into disaster. Work on loving who you are and bettering yourself everyday, then the right person for you will come along.\n- **The Ego is Taking Over. **Part of the ego is sometimes recognized as arrogance. Boy, does our generation have a sh*t ton of that. It’s all about status, money, and how many followers you have on Twitter. An overboard of selfies so a bunch of people you may or may not know can tell you how awesome you are. The other part of the ego is insecurity. Feeling insecure when you see a beautiful picture of someone else or jealousy of how someones lifestyle is displayed through imagery.\n- **Lack of Respect For One’s Self. **Sleeping around, posting half naked pictures, and pretending to be someone you are not is all just disrespecting yourself. Giving someone your mind, your body, and your soul is a beautiful experience and we suck the beauty right out of it. Sex is great and it is meant to be great, with the *right* person. A person who loves and respects you, not someone who just wants to feel great in the moment but for a *lifetime. *Wanna Netflix and chill? Nope, I want to turn off Netflix and make love, thank you very much.\n- **The World is at Our Fingertips. **Literally, by the click of a mouse we can instantly have anything we want. If we are hungry we can wait in a drive-thru for a few minutes or have it delivered to our doorsteps. Need clothes? Order them online! Millions of apps and Google search help us to not have to work for anything. Why work at being in love for a lifetime, when you can experience it in one night?\n- **Partying is More Important Than Building Lasting Relationships. **All our generation cares about is drugs and alcohol. An instant feeling of numbness to take away emotional pain, not having to face it and work through your issues is addicting. Some people drink and do drugs to intensify emotions of love and sexual desire, creating an illusion of what it’s actually really like to love someone. Thus, to work for love or wait for a lasting union is not needed.\n- **We Don’t Know How to Love. **Love has and always will be complex. Our generation isn’t the only one in history who are confused by this phenomena. Love is scary,  it makes you vulnerable and susceptible to the worst kind of pain you have ever felt. Contrary to this, love is beautiful, selfless and inspiring. Most love stories aren’t fairy tales, people have to work for it and *wait* for it. Are you willing to begin to understand love for what it actually is? Or, would you rather pretend it to be something it is not just so you can get a quick, but false taste?\n\nI’ve experienced first hand some of the issues I listed above, I’ll admit it. It taught me a lot and one day I realized I want no part of the facades our generation is becoming apart of. What about you?\n\n**About the Author: **\n\n[**Kate Rae**](http://katerae.wordpress.com) is an intuitive writer discussing the world of mental illness and how healthy living and a little humor can greatly improve your well being. Kate recently started an uplifting [**blog about anxiety**](http://katerae.wordpress.com), relationships, and holistic living that you can follow **[here](http://katerae.wordpress.com)**. Also her daily lifestyle can be followed on her instagram **[here](http://instagram.com/katerae222)**.\n\n\n	\N	<p><strong>By <a href="http://katerae.wordpress.com">Kate Rae</a></strong> <br />\n<strong>“Love, love, love…all you need is love.”– The Beatles</strong></p>\n\n<p>What will people say about our generation? ” Well, they took millions of ‘selfies’ and they put out music called ‘trap queen’…” . Wow, I really don’t ever want to be someone’s trap queen…I really don’t even understand what that is.</p>\n\n<p>As I witness some of our generation slowly begin to wake up, it gives me hope that we could be remembered for something great. I believe in soulmates and that there are certain people meant for you, at a certain time along your life path. I think, when you are your best (or close to it), you meet your unique counterpart. Who wouldn’t want to experience that?</p>\n\n<p>The more you focus on loving yourself and those around you who deserve it (and some who don’t), the more positive the vibes you are leaking out. I wish people would just realize how important love is, because love is powerful and it could save us from a world full of selfishnes