1343	b1fcf2e3-9725-4294-a233-a7077783d701	What Your Zodiac Sign Says About How You Express Anger	what-your-zodiac-sign-says-about-how-you-express-anger	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Everyone likes to express their disappointments, frustrations and anger in different ways.  Maybe you’re the type to sit in the corner and brood or maybe you’re the type to start yelling and causing a big scene.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Anger is multi-faceted emotion and there are endless ways to express it.  But your Zodiac sign also has a lot to say about how you handle yourself when you’re feeling pissed off. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here is each Zodiac sign’s way of expressing anger:</span>\n\n**Aries (March 21 – April 19) | Temper tantrums**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Aries are notorious for being firecrackers, and when it comes to anger, they’re prone to sudden outbursts.  They don’t like to sugarcoat things for anyone, so if they’re upset with you, you’ll know about it.</span>\n\n**Taurus (April 20 – May 20) | Build up and explode**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Taurus is a dangerous person to upset, as they won’t initially let you know that they’re mad at you.  They let their emotions simmer, subtly trying to give hints that you’ve upset them before letting all of their boiling anger come flowing out like an erupting volcano.</span>\n\n**Gemini (May 21 – June 20) | Verbal expression**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Because Geminis are so obsessed with talking, it should come as no surprise that their anger is unleashed via their sharp tongues.  They like to scream, shout and throw insults that cut to the very core of a person’s being.</span>\n\n**Cancer (June 21 – July 22) | Kind of all over the place**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Cancer doesn’t openly express their anger until they’ve taken all that they can handle.  First they sulk, then they become passive-aggressive, and then they become reclusive.  If no one has taken the time to try and remedy this situation, they go from crying to intense outbursts of anger.</span>\n\n**Leo (July 23 – August 22) | RAAAWR!**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Leo is quite apt at expressing anger.  When they’re pissed off, they love to shout and yell while becoming an intense storm of anger and fury.  They swear like sailors and use vulgar language during their outbursts.</span>\n\n**Virgo (August 23 – September 22) | Brood and brood**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Virgos don’t particularly enjoy letting their anger out, so what usually happens is they hold all of it in for as long as they can until something tiny lights their fuse, blowing them into orbit.  Their anger is usually never about something immediate that happened, but rather something that happened long ago.</span>\n\n**Libra (September 23 – October 22) | Seething behind the scenes**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Libras despise confrontation and hate showing their anger because they think it makes them less attractive.  They try not to let their angry emotions get to them, but sometimes they do and they will lose their cool.</span>\n\n**Scorpio (October 23 – November 21) | We are the fury**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It takes a lot to get the Scorpio fired up, but should you somehow achieve this feat, be prepared for a venomous wrath.  Scorpios are adept at destroying a person with verbal onslaughts and looks that could kill, and they’re not quick to forgive or forget what you’ve done.</span>\n\n**Sagittarius (November 22 – December 21) | One big ball of fire**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Sagittarius has no fear of turning it up to 11.  If you piss them off they’ll get rid of you in a heartbeat.  Try to distract them from their anger, as they will often lose sight of why they were even upset in the first place.</span>\n\n**Capricorn (December 22 – January 19) | Destroy everything you touch**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Capricorn isn’t likely to express anger until their threshold has been reached.  Once it has been reached though, they’re likely to want to break something, like the spirit of the person who has wronged them or that lamp in the corner over there.  </span>\n\n**Aquarius (January 20 – February 18) | Let it go, let it gooo**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Sagittarius has no chill, then the Aquarius has all of the chill.  When they’re upset they’ll simply disengage with everyone around them and go for a drive, or walk around for a bit until they’re not upset anymore.  If they can’t seem to let it go, they’ll eventually lose their temper and dump all of their negative emotions on you.</span>\n\n**Pisces (February 19 – March) | Up, down and all around**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Pisces aren’t ones to typically get very angry, which makes it all the worse when they finally do.  However, the only person they ever seem to get upset with is themselves.  Their rage includes violent, self-destructive behaviors, often requiring a bit of healing after they’re done with an outburst.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Everyone likes to express their disappointments, frustrations and anger in different ways.  Maybe you’re the type to sit in the corner and brood or maybe you’re the type to start yelling and causing a big scene.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Anger is multi-faceted emotion and there are endless ways to express it.  But your Zodiac sign also has a lot to say about how you handle yourself when you’re feeling pissed off. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here is each Zodiac sign’s way of expressing anger:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Aries (March 21 – April 19) | Temper tantrums</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Aries are notorious for being firecrackers, and when it comes to anger, they’re prone to sudden outbursts.  They don’t like to sugarcoat things for anyone, so if they’re upset with yo