1407	b5826b5a-194b-4035-a43d-7ed122ddef51	5 Things That People Regret the Most When They Are On Their Deathbed	5-things-that-people-regret-the-most-when-they-are-on-their-deathbed	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">As human beings, we all come with an expiration date.  It’s a natural part of life, one that we’ve struggled to cope with for generations.  In fact, right now, somewhere in the world, there is probably a researcher or scientist who is entirely focused on prolonging the duration of human life.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When we look at the grand scheme of things, mankind seems small.  We’re only here for a blink of the eye.  Which makes many people regretful of the life they lived up until their moment of passing.  Feeling as though they simply didn’t </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">do</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> enough during their time here.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">There is still time to live fully and happily, but you have to make the choice right now.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five of the most common regrets from people who are on their deathbeds:</span>\n\n**I wish I had cared more for the people who mattered the most**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">We all know what it’s like to hurt the person you love the most in this world.  Even with good intentions, sometimes we fall short.  Many people regret not being there for the people who were the most important to them.  They wished they had said ‘I love you’ more often and to more people.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Always take the time out of your day to tell people you care about just how much you appreciate them.</span>\n\n**I wish I had been a better parent, spouse, child, etc.**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Family is one of the most common things people believe they take for granted.  Especially once they start (or do not start) to show tremendous care for you once you’re nearing death.  Familial r