1319	c2845a6d-c55c-4508-817e-f55f15f4371c	Soulmate or Life Partner, Do You Know the Difference?	soulmate-or-life-partner-do-you-know-the-difference	\n**[Longing to find one’s soulmate](http://foreverconscious.com/why-do-we-seek-companionship)** is often the tale of many Disney films, romantic films, and fairy tales.  But the idea is so inherently good-natured and lovable.  Doesn’t everyone like to think that there is one person out there who is just absolutely perfect for them in every way?  It’s what keeps many of us chasing after true love, even after our hearts have been broken over and over again.\n\nWhat is a soulmate, though?  According to **[ForeverConscious](http://foreverconscious.com/the-difference-between-soulmates-and-life-partners)**, a soulmate is one who is aligned with your soul and is sent to challenge, awaken and stir different parts of your in order for your soul to transcend to higher levels of consciousness and awareness, and once the lesson has been learned, the two beings physically separate.\n\nA life partner is a companion and friend, a stable person who you can always rely on, trust, and depend on to help you through the trials of life.  You share a mutual love and respect for one another, always in sync, satisfying each others needs and desires.\n\nSoulmates appear in our lives at the exact moment when we need them.  When we are ready to learn one of the grand lessons in life, our soulmates are there to guide us toward the destiny we were meant to live.  Soulmate relationships typically do not stand the test of time, as they are typically too intense and possess a certain karmic energy necessary to close relationships once the lessons have been learned.\n\nThey are not always romantic partners, they can be friends or relatives.  You will, however, always feel a strong connection to these individuals, as you have a shared energy or a past life history with one another.\n\nOn the other hand, a life partner is someone who acts more as companion or friend.  While you might not feel that deep, soulful connection that you would normally with a soulmate, but a life partner provides a mutual trust and understanding of one another.  They respect your desires and needs and love and care for you.\n\nManifesting a life partner in your life is not a spiritual process like with our soulmates.  They are there to provide support and guidance as you continue on your own journey through life, just as you are there for them in the same way.  Meeting your life partner happens when you are both emotionally and mentally prepared, putting yourself into the world with confidence in your being.\n\n**[It is not impossible for a soulmate to become a life partner](http://foreverconscious.com/why-you-may-not-want-to-marry-your-soulmate)** and life partners are fully capable for developing deep, soulful connections, it all depends on the specific people and circumstances.\n\nCheck out the different characteristics of each type of relationship:\n\n**Soulmate Relationship**\n\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel a deep, spiritual connection to this person almost like you have known them for a long time.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You have flashbacks or deja vu moments where you feel that you have been together before.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You seem to understand each other and have a similar way of thinking.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You may have similar flaws or habits, or you both had similar challenges during childhood.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Your connection is intense and so too is the relationship. Often it can move from extreme highs to extreme lows.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel in sync with each other even when you are not physically together. There may be a feeling of having to team up together to conquer something.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You know intuitively what the other is thinking or feeling. You feel very in-tune and connected with their thoughts and actions.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship is emotional, challenging and can bring things out in you that you didn’t know existed.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You may experience huge shifts and changes in your life when you first meet this person.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship may not last forever but the love is always there.</span>\n\n**Life Partner Relationship**\n\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel attracted to each other physically and resonate with each others values.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You enjoy getting to know each other and learn about your differences and similarities- everything about each other feels new and exciting.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You get along like best friends- your relationship does not suffer from extremes.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship is based on logical or intellectual decisions.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You resonate with each others beliefs, ideas or religion/philosophy.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You both feel a sense of financial and emotional stability by being together.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship is based on being physically present and creating new memories.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel the need to marry or start a family in order to ‘cement’ your relationship.</span>\n\n(h/t [**Forever Conscious**](http://foreverconscious.com/the-difference-between-soulmates-and-life-partners))\n\n\n	\N	<p><strong><a href="http://foreverconscious.com/why-do-we-seek-companionship">Longing to find one’s soulmate</a></strong> is often the tale of many Disney films, romantic films, and fairy tales.  But the idea is so inherently good-natured and lovable.  Doesn’t everyone like to think that there is one person out there who is just absolutely perfect for them in every 