urney through life, just as you are there for them in the same way.  Meeting your life partner happens when you are both emotionally and mentally prepared, putting yourself into the world with confidence in your being.</p>\n\n<p><strong><a href="http://foreverconscious.com/why-you-may-not-want-to-marry-your-soulmate">It is not impossible for a soulmate to become a life partner</a></strong> and life partners are fully capable for developing deep, soulful connections, it all depends on the specific people and circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>Check out the different characteristics of each type of relationship:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Soulmate Relationship</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel a deep, spiritual connection to this person almost like you have known them for a long time.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You have flashbacks or deja vu moments where you feel that you have been together before.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You seem to understand each other and have a similar way of thinking.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You may have similar flaws or habits, or you both had similar challenges during childhood.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Your connection is intense and so too is the relationship. Often it can move from extreme highs to extreme lows.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel in sync with each other even when you are not physically together. There may be a feeling of having to team up together to conquer something.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You know intuitively what the other is thinking or feeling. You feel very in-tune and connected with their thoughts and actions.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship is emotional, challenging and can bring things out in you that you didn’t know existed.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You may experience huge shifts and changes in your life when you first meet this person.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship may not last forever but the love is always there.</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Life Partner Relationship</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel attracted to each other physically and resonate with each others values.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You enjoy getting to know each other and learn about your differences and similarities- everything about each other feels new and exciting.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You get along like best friends- your relationship does not suffer from extremes.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship is based on logical or intellectual decisions.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You resonate with each others beliefs, ideas or religion/philosophy.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You both feel a sense of financial and emotional stability by being together.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Your relationship is based on being physically present and creating new memories.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You feel the need to marry or start a family in order to ‘cement’ your relationship.</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>(h/t <a href="http://foreverconscious.com/the-difference-between-soulmates-and-life-partners"><strong>Forever Conscious</strong></a>)</p>	http://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2016/03/feature_image_tedifffmplate.jpg	f	f	published	en_US	public	\N	\N	1	2016-03-08 06:53:43+00	1	2016-03-08 06:53:43+00	1	2016-03-08 06:53:43+00	1
1375	5b9cac3f-ec88-4958-8e39-ef3435943946	Relieve Sinus Pressure in Under 30 Seconds With This Simple Method	relieve-sinus-pressure-in-under-30-seconds-with-this-simple-method	\n \n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">With us working our way through Spring and heading into Summer with full force, allergy season is upon us.  These are the times when most of our allergies start to flare up, causing us tremendous amounts of agony and suffering at the hands of congested airways, itchy eyes and sinuses full of pressure.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re rife with allergies like myself, then you know just how horrible it can be.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">But you can prepare yourself at least a little bit by adding this simple method to your arsenal of allergy relief solutions.  And while it might not fix your sinus problems in a permanent way, it will at least relieve some of that sinus congestion that you’re experiencing at the time.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re trying to keep sinus congestion to a minimum, spicy foods and drinking a ton of water are other great ways to help keep pressure from building up.</span>\n\n**The Method**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When you do this technique, your sinuses will most likely drain almost instantly.  This method works due to the movement of the vomer bone, which rests in your nasal passage.  This bone is capable of swinging back and forth with the pressure, which in turn loosens up the phlegm and grossness stuck in your sinuses.</span>\n\n1. <span style="font-weight: 400;">Press your tongue to the roof of your mouth and apply pressure (not too much).</span>\n2. <span style="font-weight: 400;">Press your thumb between your eyebrows</span>\n3. <span style="font-weight: 400;">Press your thumb down for 30 seconds while applying a fair amount of pressure</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Pretty sweet, right?  Remember this method the next time you or your friend’s sinuses are chock-full of phlegm and you find yourself hating life!</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">With us working our way through Spring and heading into Summer with full force, allergy season is upon us.  These are the times when most of our allergies start to flare up, causing us tremendous amounts of agony and suffering at the hands of congested airways, itchy eyes and sinuses full of pressure.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re rife with allergies like myself, then you know just how horrible it can be.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">But you can prepare yourself at least a little bit by adding this simple method to your arsenal of allergy relief solutions.  And while it might not fix your sinus problems in a permanent way, it will at least relieve some of that sinus congestion that you’re experiencing at the time.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re trying to keep sinus congestion to a minimum, spicy foods and drinking a ton of water are other great ways to help keep pressure from building up.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>The Method</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you do this technique, your sinuses will most likely drain almost instantly.  This method works due to the movement of the vomer bone, which rests in your nasal passage.  This bone is capable of swinging back and forth with the pressure, which in turn loosens up the phlegm and grossness stuck in your sinuses.</span></p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Press your tongue to the roof of your mouth and apply pressure (not too much).</span>  </li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Press your thumb between your eyebrows</span>  </li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Press your thumb down for 30 seconds while applying a fair amount of pressure</span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pretty sweet, right?  Remember this method the next time you or your friend’s sinuses are chock-full of phlegm and you find yourself hating life!</span></p>	http://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2016/05/feature_image_tearemplate.jpg	f	f	published	en_US	public	\N	\N	1	2016-05-09 06:29:37+00	1	2016-05-09 06:29:37+00	1	2016-05-09 06:29:37+00	1
