1324	7de0e4e3-fbbe-491b-94f2-2b274de326c8	Only 1 in 4 People Can See Every Color in This Box, How Many Do You See?	only-1-in-4-people-can-see-every-color-in-this-box-how-many-do-you-see	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s interesting to think that there are 7 billion people on this planet, each living a unique life, filled with unique experiences, senses, thoughts, beliefs.  And not a single one of us will ever know what it’s like to be someone else.  You can’t even try to imagine what it would be like because you just </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">don’t know</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So, what if I told you that the sky is green?  I’m sure you’d vehemently deny my claim and suggest that it’s actually blue, but what if for me it actually was green?  Maybe my greens are your blues and my yellows are your reds.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Remember the heart-attack that **[the internet had over the color of a dress](http://www.littlethings.com/what-colors-are-this-dress/)** not too long ago?  Half the population said the dress was white and gold, the other half said it was blue and black.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Well, it turns out that it all has to do with how many color receptors you have in your eyeballs.  [Diana Derval](https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/25-people-have-4th-cone-see-colors-p-prof-diana-derval), a neuro-marketing expert, has developed a little test to determine how color-sensitive your eyes are.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">How many of the colors can you find in the box below?</span>\n\n**Count the colors in the box**\n\n![To take the test, count the colors you see in this spectrum:](http://cdn6.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/05/d45f74fc-9a3a-48e9-89e2-7f6816afd066-600x315.jpg)\n\n**So, how many were you able to count?**\n\n**Fewer than 20 colors – **<span style="font-weight: 400;">This number represents people who only have two cones 