ing enough, and courageous enough to take on any endeavor.</span>\n\n**You’re perfectly okay as you are right now**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Changing who you are for reasons that are not true to yourself is not healthy growth.  Transformation is a choice, but it must come to us organically and from a place of acceptance.  Be content with who you are and your transformative process will occur on its own.</span>\n\n**Self worth is measured by the self**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You can look to others for happiness through approval and validation, but true happiness does not lie within others.  Each one of the 7 billion people living on our planet today is unique and complex, and the people in your life are no different.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Striving to make each and every person happy just isn’t a possible goal.  Make yourself happy first and foremost, and then you can start to make others happy.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The soul is often talked about like it’s something that is separate from the rest of our being, but the truth is that our souls are our true existence in this world.  When we forget that we are shadows of our souls, we forget what it means to truly be ourselves, where we truly come from and how to be all that we can be.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When this happens, it’s okay, because our souls have got our backs, and they’ll always be there to guide us along by reminding us of these five simple life truths:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You are where you are supposed to be, do not fret</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you’re working your way through life, making big decisions, and choosing which paths to take at those monumental forks in the road, your soul knows that regardless of which choices you make, at the end of the day everything happens for a reason.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Embrace where you are at this momen