1339	4a66861a-5d0d-48e6-bac1-804b6980669e	5 Tips for Communicating Telepathically with Animals	5-tips-for-communicating-telepathically-with-animals	\n<span class="s1">While it might seem far-fetched at first, Dr. Linda Bender says that telepathy between yourself and animals is possible and she’ll help you do it.  In order to create the space in which one communicates telepathically with an animal, one must first quiet the mind, focus on living presently, and open the heart.  Once you’ve done this, practice doing one or more of the practices below for at least a few minutes a day.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Animals mainly think in pictures and emotions.  So, when they’re trying to connect with you, they’ll often create a mental image or some type of emotion.  Communicating with animals isn’t like talking to a friend over the phone.  You will not ‘hear’ their words, necessarily, but rather different words will manifest in your own mind spontaneously as you receive their thoughts or feelings.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Here are five practices for telepathy with animals:</span>\n\n<span class="s1">**Pictorial Messages**</span>\n\n<span class="s1">When trying to get your animal companion to do something for you, next time try forming a mental image of the action that you want them to do, and then focus on sending that image to them via ‘telepathic airwaves’.  </span>\n\n<span class="s1">Like in those old beer commercials, where the dog fetches a beer for his master out of the fridge, picture them doing whatever it is you want them to do.  You’ll start to notice that they respond to these mental messages.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">**Sending Feelings**</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Similar to the last practice, you’ll be trying to send your emotions or feelings to your animal companion.  To try this, instead of exclaiming ‘good boy!’, practice focusing more on the actual feeling of being happy or satisfied with your companion.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Once you’ve really built up this emotion of being pleased inside of you, send it off to them.  Practicing this will help you both send and receive messages from animals.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">**Make a Metaphor**</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Being able to create different metaphors is vital to understanding metaphors that you might receive from an animal.  Metaphors are mental images that symbolically represent certain feelings, emotions, or ideas.  </span>\n\n<span class="s1">For example, if I’m feeling overwhelmed in life, an image of Atlas holding the Earth on his shoulders might pop into my mind.  Practice creating different mental images of metaphors for the feelings you experience, as animals will often use these to try to speak to you.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">**Send Comfort**</span>\n\n<span class="s1">In the same way that you would send a mental image or a feeling, sending comfort is one of the best ways to get through to an animal telepathically.  Focus on the animal’s suffering and then brainstorm all of the ways you can offer it comfort.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">You can send feelings of being loved or pictures of you soothing them or petting them.  If the animal is near death you might send them images of how happy they’ll be in their new afterlife animal sanctuary.  Gather these thoughts and feelings, prepare them to be sent and then shoot them over to the animal in need.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">**Requests for Help**</span>\n\n<span class="s1">While animals have no way of interpreting any sort of spoken message, they’re very apt at picking up on the emotions and feelings that lie behind them.  When a person asks for help, they typically expect a solution to be given in the form of a spoken answer, “you need to do this.”  Animals will not be able to answer questions like this.  </span>\n\n<span class="s1">Instead, focus on a current problem or concern that you have and then navigate your way through all of the different feelings and emotions that have motivated the question.  Use these feelings to build a statement instead of a question, acknowledge any images that come with it, and then telepathically send that statement (along with any emotions or pictures) to an animal, to yourself, to another person, or to your God.  </span>\n\n \n\n(h/t **[OM Times](http://omtimes.com/2015/06/telepathy-with-animals/4/)**)\n\n\n	\N	<p><span class="s1">While it might seem far-fetched at first, Dr. Linda Bender says that telepathy between yourself and animals is possible and she’ll help you do it.  In order to create the space in which one communicates telepathically with an animal, one must first quiet the mind, focus on living presently, and open the heart.  Once you’ve done this, practice doing one or more of the practices below for at least a few minutes a day.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Animals mainly think in pictures and emotions.  So, when they’re trying to connect with you, they’ll often create a mental image or some type of emotion.  Communicating with animals isn’t like talking to a friend over the phone.  You will not ‘hear’ their words, necessarily, but rather different words will manifest in your own mind spontaneously as you receive their thoughts or feelings.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Here are five practices for telepathy with animals:</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1"><strong>Pictorial Messages</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">When trying to get your animal companion to do something for you, next time try forming a mental image of the action that you want them to do, and then focus on sending that image to them via ‘telepathic airwaves’.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Like in those old beer commercials, where the dog fetches a beer for his master out of the fridge, picture them doing whatever it is you want them to do.  You’ll start to notice that they respond to these mental messages.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1"><strong>Sending Feelings</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Similar t