1346	ec4b2e21-764b-4a17-b707-a3f990ad0b09	5 Great Ways to Clear Negative Energy From Your Home	5-great-ways-to-clear-negative-energy-from-your-home	\nNegative energies often accumulate in the spaces that we neglect and forget to take the time for.  Our homes like to reflect how the rest of our lives are doing, meaning if we’re in a poor place, our homes are likely to be as well.  Don’t let yourself become overwhelmed with negativity.\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Try these five easy tips for clearing out the negative energies in your home so you can start living a more positive lifestyle:</span>\n\n**Make your space exist for you**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">As time goes by, many of us pick up lots of additional baggage that we might not want in our homes, but feel pressured to keep anyway because they are gifts or hold value for someone else.  If there’s anything in your home that you feel obligated to keep around, get rid of it.  Build a space that features only things that </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">you</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> want and like.</span>\n\n**Try clapping in the corners**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Stagnant energy is quickly gotten rid of by clapping in the corners of each room you want to affect.  Maybe there are certain spaces in your home that feel naturally depressed or stagnant, clap in their corners until you feel a shift in the energy.</span>\n\n**Fix your broken things**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’ve stopped using certain items in your home that you used to use all the time, but now can’t because they are broken, take the time to fix them.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you can’t afford to fix everything immediately, no worries, just form a plan or have intentions to fix them once you can.  Doing your best always promotes positive energy.</span>\n\n**Fill your kitchen with ‘good’**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the same way that your body starts to feel better once you’ve filled it largely with superfoods, nutrients and other healthy substances, your kitchen’s energy will do the same thing if you fill it with the things that are great for you.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Stock your kitchen with plant-based foods, unprocessed snacks, and pure pantry ingredients, and you’ll notice a huge difference in energy.</span>\n\n**Do everything with love**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It is widely believed that love has both effective and universal healing properties, so adding more of it to your life can only benefit you.  The most effective way to keep negative energy out of the home is to take the time to do the activities you love in your home.  It could be a quiet nook for reading, a master chef’s kitchen, or an outside patio that you relax on.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Removing all of the negative energy from one’s space allows for positive things to grow there instead, like love, peace, fun, health and prosperity.</span>\n\n(h/t**[ Mind Body Green](http://www.mindbodygreen.com/0-24379/5-easy-ways-to-clear-your-home-of-negative-energy-now.html)**)\n\n\n	\N	<p>Negative energies often accumulate in the spaces that we neglect and forget to take the time for.  Our homes like to reflect how the rest of our lives are doing, meaning if we’re in a poor place, our homes are likely to be as well.  Don’t let yourself become overwhelmed with negativity.</p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Try these five easy tips for clearing out the negative energies in your home so you can start living a more positive lifestyle:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Make your space exist for you</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">As time goes by, many of us pick up lots of additional baggage that we might not want in our homes, but feel pressured to keep anyway because they are gifts or hold value for someone else.  If there’s anything in your home that you feel obligated to keep around, get rid of it.