1356	2bed5a6b-135d-41a4-a64d-b24e9d9ede09	5 Signs You've Found the Right Relationship	5-signs-youve-found-the-right-relationship	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sometimes it’s easy to tell when a relationship just isn’t heading in the right direction.  Sometimes things are going great when a sudden patch of roughness turns things upside down, leaving the two of you reeling and confused.  It can be hard to tell if you should stick it out or decide to part ways.  But there are little things that let you know the two of you are doing things right.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five ways to tell that you’re in a relationship that’s right for you:</span>\n\n**You have the support of others**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Friends and family are the ones we turn to for acceptance of our choice in partner because we trust that they only want the best for us, and because they’re outside of the relationship so they can see things a little more clearly.  If your friends and family want to see you and your partner together, there’s something to be said about that.  Don’t get too caught up with what others think, but it is a good sign.</span>\n\n**You guys fight fairly**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s a good thing if the two of you can have conflicts that do not resort to personal attacks and/or insults.  If your arguments are focused mainly on resolving known issues while still considering each other’s feelings and desires, then it’s a good sign that the two of you are good for each other.</span>\n\n**You’re growing together**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Any great relationship is great because there is growth by both people involved.  When the two of you do not inhibit one another’s emotional, mental and spiritual growth, then it’s a good sign that you’re meant to be together.</span>\n\n**You view each other as life partners**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When you can’t imagine a life without your significant other it’s very telling of how deeply you care about them.  If you struggle to imagine a world where the two of you aren’t together in some form or another, and know that your partner feels the same way, you’re in the right relationship.</span>\n\n**You’re not interested in another love**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">While there are all types of love in this world, each of them different, you can’t imagine yourself loving anyone but your partner.  Physical attractions will come and go harmlessly as long as we acknowledge them for what they are, and then let them go.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When you’re positive that no other bond in the world can compare to the connection the two of you have, it’s a good sign you’ve found the right relationship.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sometimes it’s easy to tell when a relationship just isn’t heading in the right direction.  Sometimes things are going great when a sudden patch of roughness turns things upside down, leaving the two of you reeling and confused.  It can be hard to tell if you should stick it out or decide to part ways.  But there are little things that let you know the two of you are doing things right.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five ways to tell that you’re in a relationship that’s right for you:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You have the support of others</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Friends and family are the ones we turn to for acceptance of our choice in partner because we trust that they only want the best for us, and because they’re outside of the relationship so they can see things a little more clearly.  If your friends and family want to see you and your partner together, there’s something to be said about that.  Don’t get too caught up with what others think, but it is a good sign.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You guys fight fairly</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s a good thing if the two of you can have conflicts that do not resort to personal attacks and/or insults.  If your arguments are focused mainly on resolving known issues while still considering each other’s feelings and desires, then it’s a good sign that the two of you are good for each other.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You’re growing together</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Any great relationship is great because there is growth by both people involved.  When the two of you do not inhibit one another’s emotional, mental and spiritual growth, then it’s a good sign that you’re meant to be together.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You view each other as life partners</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you can’t imagine a life without your significant other it’s very telling of how deeply you care about them.  If you struggle to imagine a world where the two of you aren’t together in some form or another, and know that your partner feels the same way, you’re in the right relationship.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You’re not interested in another love</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">While there are all types of love in this world, each of them different, you can’t imagine yourself loving anyone but your partner.  Physical attractions will come and go harmlessly as long as we acknowledge them for what they are, and then let them go.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you’re positive that no other bond in the world can compare to the connection the two of you have, it’s a good sign you’ve found the right relationship.</span></p>	http://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2016/04/feature_imageasedfrs_template.jpg	f	f	published	en_US	public	\N	\N	1	2016-04-19 21:16:28+00	1	2016-04-19 21:16:28+00	1	2016-04-19 21:16:28+00	1
1406	8a445cb8-6d6e-4dc9-ac27-c295d3c46c2e	5 Forgotten Truths to Remember During Hard Times	5-forgotten-truths-to-remember-during-hard-times	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The nature of life is simply that there will be good times and there will undoubtedly be bad times; it’s how we react, how we compose ourselves during these times that come to define our true character.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When we find ourselves in these unfortunate situations, we can let them take hold of us and destroy us, or we can use them to fortify ourselves, to bolster our being.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">These five forgotten truths are empowering–they’ll help you remain strong and wise during troubled times.</span>\n\n**Pain is a natural part of life, it helps you grow**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It could be argued that pain is </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">the</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> most natural part of human life.  But without pain, we would not have growth.  Pain shows us what we are truly capable of overcoming, it wakes us up to our truest of feelings.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So, embrace pain, embrace your scars and wounds as you move forward and flourish into the truest version of yourself.</span>\n\n**Change your perspective, change your world**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you believe life is good, then life is good.  If you believe life is bad, then life is bad.  You can be happy if you want to be, as being happy is a skill, one that many people learn to master slowly over their lives.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">They take nothing for granted, treat every day as a gift, and never let anything bitter take away from anything sweet.</span>\n\n**A large part of growth happens through experience**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">A great lesson in life is learning to never assume or expect anything, because life often has other plans.  And what you gain from these ‘other’ plans, is experience.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Experience is incredibly valuable, it gives us strength, wisdom, and courage.  Know that all of your experiences up to this point have prepared you for everything that has yet to come.</span>\n\n**You only have to live in the present**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">While most of us often get caught up living in some idealistic future, or terrifying past, life is lived in the passing seconds of each moment of each day.  To achieve any sort of goal or vision of tomorrow, the work has to be put in today.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Don’t get caught up on where you think you should be–you are exactly where you need to be right now, and it’s going to take you to where you want to be in the future.</span>\n\n**You will never find true validation from other people**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the most empowering truths of life is that we do not exist in this world for other people.  You do not owe anyone anything, so never feel like you have to live your life according to anyone but yourself.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you seek status, wealth and fame, or solitude, peace and quiet, it is your decision, no one else’s.  Define success for yourself, and then succeed.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The nature of life is simply that there will be good times and there will undoubtedly be bad times; it’s how we react, how we compose ourselves during these times that come to define our true character.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When we find ourselves in these unfortunate situations, we can let them take hold of us and destroy us, or we can use them to fortify ourselves, to bolster our being.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">These five forgotten truths are empowering–they’ll help you remain strong and wise during troubled times.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Pain is a natural part of life, it helps you grow</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It could be argued that pain is </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> most natural part of human life.  But without pain, we would not have growth.  Pain shows us what we are truly capable of overcoming, it wakes us up to our truest of feelings.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">So, embrace pain, embrace your scars and wounds as you move forward and flourish into the truest version of yourself.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Change your perspective, change your world</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you believe life is good, then life is good.  If you believe life is bad, then life is bad.  You can be happy if you want to be, as being happy is a skill, one that many people learn to master slowly over their lives.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">They take nothing for granted, treat every day as a gift, and never let anything bitter take away from anything sweet.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>A large part of growth happens through experience</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A great lesson in life is learning to never assume or expect anything, because life often has other plans.  And what you gain from these ‘other’ plans, is experience.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Experience is incredibly valuable, it gives us strength, wisdom, and courage.  Know that all of your experiences up to this point have prepared you for everything that has yet to come.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You only have to live in the present</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">While most of us often get caught up living in some idealistic future, or terrifying past, life is lived in the passing seconds of each moment of each day.  To achieve any sort of goal or vision of tomorrow, the work has to be put in today.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Don’t get caught up on where you think you should be–you are exactly where you need to be right now, and it’s going to take you to where you want to be in the future.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You will never find true validation from other people</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the most empowering truths of life is that we do not exist in this world for other people.  You do not owe anyone anything, so never feel like you have to live your life according to anyone but yourself.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you seek status, wealth and fame, or solitude, peace and quiet, it is your decision, no one else’s.  Define success for yourself, and then succeed.</span></p>	http://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2016/05/feature_image_te555mplate.jpg	f	f	published	en_US	public	\N	\N	1	2016-05-30 07:36:08+00	1	2016-05-30 07:36:08+00	1	2016-05-30 07:36:08+00	1
