1370	422fa629-6d39-4739-b36f-10b534ce7b3f	Gaslighting: The Mind Game Everyone Should Know About	gaslighting-the-mind-game-everyone-should-know-about	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’ve ever been the victim or subject of the manipulation tool known as ‘gaslighting,’ then you know just how awful it can truly be.  While this tactic is largely described as “sophisticated,” it only takes on this label because of how truly insane it really is.  It is used by malicious personality types to manifest fear and doubt in the minds of others.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are the people that use it, how it works and what you should be looking out for:</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The term ‘gaslighting’ actually **[comes from a 1930s film](http://www.theearthchild.co.za/gaslighting-as-a-manipulation-tactic-what-it-is-who-does-it-and-why/)** in which a scheming husband tries to get rid of his wife by slowly making subtle changes to her environment (including dimming the flame on a gas lamp slightly over time) to make her think that she’s losing her mind.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It is now used to describe a similar process often practiced by sociopaths, narcissists and psychopaths who seek to build up so much doubt in a person’s mind that this victim starts to believe that they cannot trust their own judgments, decisions or thoughts anymore, and thus starts to look to the psychopath for answers.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Gaslighting is often paired with other destructive tactics, like guilting and shaming.  It is achieved in a variety of different ways, like when a person states a major lie with such conviction that the victim questions their perception of reality.  Similarly, they’ll often deny events or experiences ever happened with an intense and determined fervor.  They like to use historical facts that sound accurate, but then tweak them slightly to favor their argument or to seem credible.</span>\n\n