1377	40f88d92-96e2-4e44-8067-61870f2e1a16	5 Subtle and Surprising Ways That Your Dog is Saying 'I Love You'	5-subtle-and-surprising-ways-that-your-dog-is-saying-i-love-you	\n \n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re a dog owner then you know just how rewarding it can be.  Dogs are known as “man’s best friend” for a reason, because they’ve been our trusted sidekicks for as long as we can remember.  And as it turns out, all of the time that we’ve spent together over the centuries has led to dogs developing unique and subtle ways of expressing their love for us.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">While we might not be able to communicate with them like Doctor Dolittle, we will at least know when they’re feeling loved and want to give some love back.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The ways that they express their love are not always obvious, but we’ll discuss at least five different practices they like to do to show their human companions love and support:</span>\n\n**Staring straight into your eyes**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to a </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">60 Minutes </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">segment featuring well-known dog expert, Brian Hare, when dogs look you in the eye, they’re actually “hugging you with [their] eyes.”  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When you and your buddy are playing together or having a nice cuddle session, the same hormone that helps mothers and babies bond, oxytocin, is released in the dog’s brain.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Try keeping eye consistent eye contact with them as you go about your normal daily routine with them, but do not actively stare them down, as it will only make them feel uncomfortable.</span>\n\n**Sharing yawns**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">We all know that yawning is one of the most contagious things in the world, but what you might not have known is that it’s not limited to humans.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-we