1414	79247554-201c-4353-bb11-e7588e8a0d62	5 Things To Quit Stressing Over As Soon As Possible	5-things-to-quit-stressing-over-as-soon-as-possible	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Have you ever thought about all of the little (and big) things that you stress about on a regular basis?  Some worries for me include: my student loans, making enough money to support myself, making enough money to have fun, having enough time to do the things I like to do, keeping my relationships healthy and happy, keeping myself happy.. The list goes on and on.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Worrying about things does absolutely nothing for us.  Think about it.  Are you achieving anything when you sit and stress over things that have yet to happen?  Worry does not relieve the burdens of tomorrow, it only limits what you are capable of today.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So, take action, be assertive, be proactive, and stop worrying about these five things immediately:</span>\n\n**Challenges**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Every single challenge you come across in life is an opportunity for growth.  What would life be without challenges?  They’re what keep our lives interesting, and we gain a sense of self by overcoming them.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When we landed a man on the moon, we did it because of the challenge.  To say that we did it.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Recognize challenges for what they are and use them to grow stronger, to live more fully.</span>\n\n**Poor circumstances that are out of your control**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Know that even during the seemingly darkest of times, you still have the ability to not only succeed, but to thrive.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">We are all capable of extraordinary things, but many of us never do them because we have excuses.  The economy is bad, the weather is crappy outside today, etc.  The only thing that you have control over at the end of the day is your mind, so use it to overcome.</span>\n\n**What everyone else is doing**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">I read somewhere recently that people who were not on social media tended to be less depressed than those who were because they weren’t constantly comparing their lives to others’.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Don’t let the image of others succeeding and doing well deter you from chasing your own happiness.  They are encouraging you to do the same with your life as they are doing with theirs.  Don’t let your potential fade away, start doing everything you’ve always wanted to do today.</span>\n\n**Any hollow or shallow love interests**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re in a relationship with someone who you feel isn’t fully invested in you, your life and your dreams, then you don’t have time for it.  True love comes after the honeymoon period, after the initial lust that we feel when we fall.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s an uphill climb that takes dedicated attention, awareness, discipline, effort and compromise.  It’s loving someone even during the worst of times that matters.</span>\n\n**Working only for the sake of money**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Many people are solely focused on get-rich-quick schemes so that they can spend the rest of their lives in leisure and without worry.  What they fail to realize is that one can achieve leisure and get rid of worries by embracing the things they are passionate about in this life.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Use the things that inspire you, that move you, that motivate you, to create a wonderful life for yourself.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Have you ever thought about all of the little (and big) things that you stress about on a regular basis?  Some worries for me include: my student loans, making enough money to support myself, making enough money to have fun, having enough time to do the things I like to