nant and give birth to a calf.  In the dairy industry, however, it is commonplace for young calves to be taken from their mothers shortly after birth in order for the mother’s milk to be collected.\n\nEmma’s retired as a dairy cow nowadays, along with the other cows that have been rescued and brought to the sanctuary.  She gets to live a happy, pregnant-free life alongside her newly found cow family.\n\nh/t **[sun gazing](http://www.sun-gazing.com/cow-terrified-started-crying-realized-headed/)**\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">As a highly-sensitive and empathetic individual, seeing any being or creature in pain or despair causes me to feel similarly.  Seeing the image of this poor, terrified cow, who undoubtedly feels tremendous fear about what’s going to happen to her, makes my heart hurt.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">My initial thoughts were that this cow is headed to a slaughterhouse or somewhere to be disposed of, because the the typical narrative when it comes to sad stories about dairy animals.</span></p>\n\n<p>But, this isn’t that story.  This cow didn’t find herself in a slaughterhouse, trembling before meeting her maker.</p>\n\n<p>This dairy cow, named Emma, was loaded onto a trailer and driven to her new home at the Kuhrettung Rhein-Berg Sanctuary in Germany.  The dairy farm that was formerly her home had recently closed down, and she was slated for the chopping block at the local slaughterhouse before her rescuers intervened.</p>\n\n<iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="658" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/bLeLQ2EUv_E?feature=oembed" width="1170"></iframe>\n\n<p>At the start of the video, you can see that she is clearly in distress, shedding tears of sadness and fear.  Her heartbreaking demeanor and mannerisms are enough to shake even the most resilient of folks.  But her fears would eventually fade away, as she made her way into the spacious new pasture she would begin to call home.</p>\n\n<p>Filled with 