1402	69ad6ea4-ff99-4d3b-9e13-238bdd415c3b	5 Signs You're In a Relationship With the Right Person	5-signs-youre-in-a-relationship-with-the-right-person	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Relationships are hard work, especially if you think you’ve found the right person.  Sometimes it’s blatantly obvious when the two of you aren’t meant to be, other times it feels right, but you’re just not sure.  I guess it all really comes down to what you’re looking for in a partner.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">But there are also certain things that indicate you’ve found a healthy and happy relationship, regardless of what you think you’re looking for.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five signs that you’re in the right relationship:</span>\n\n**There’s a lack of games being played by both people**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Because love makes us act and think in rather dumb ways sometimes, we oftentimes get caught up turning seemingly mundane activities into games to be won.  Who says ‘I love you’ first?  Who texts the other one first or more often?  Making the other person jealous because you feel slighted.  The list goes on.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If your relationship is void of any game playing then it’s a good sign that you’re with the right person.</span>\n\n**You’re both on the same page**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sometimes relationships start out as casual affairs, dating here and there, but never officially a thing.  If both people want a casual relationship, then it should be agreed upon that that’s what is going to happen.  Otherwise, things can get messy and fast.  Always be straightforward and clear with your partner as to what it is that you want from the relationship.  </span>\n\n**You communicate with each other honestly and openly**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the greatest things a couple can understand is that the other person will never be able to read your mind, so unless you communicate with them how you’re feeling or what you’re thinking, nothing will get done.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When you trust each other, communication comes easy.</span>\n\n**You can balance freedom and teamwork**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When both of you feel free while also being together, it is a good sign that you’re in the right relationship.  Feeling trapped in a relationship means the relationship doesn’t truly exist.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If the two of you can work together, by meeting halfway, you will achieve more than you could by yourself.  Be willing to adjust for one another when the situation calls for it.</span>\n\n**You don’t let others influence your relationship**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">For whatever reasons, some people will find a problem with your relationship.  Sometimes they simply don’t make sense to people who are on the outside of it.  So, you’re occasionally going to run into some resistance, but never let anyone outside of your relationship ruin the relationship.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re having problems with a partner, work it out with them, and only them.  Don’t worry what others think as long as the two of you are happy.</span>\n\n(h/t **[Marc and Angel](http://www.marcandangel.com/2014/02/12/9-good-signs-youre-in-the-right-relationship/)**)\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Relationships are hard work, especially if you think you’ve found the right person.  Sometimes it’s blatantly obvious when the two of you aren’t meant to be, other times it feels right, but you’re just not sure.  I guess it all really comes down to what you’re looking for in a partner.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">But there are also certain things that indicate you’ve found a healthy and happy relationship, regardless of what you think you’re looking for.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five signs that you’re in the