1409	67f4e126-2dec-4bba-b348-c8ac06088058	5 Things to Remember When Life Gets Rough	5-things-to-remember-when-life-gets-rough	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If life is a series of ups and downs like everyone says it is, sometimes life has an odd way of showing it.  I know many of us are probably wondering when the ‘ups’ are going to show up and get rid of all the downs.  Life isn’t always easy.  And no one told you it was going to be.  The only thing anyone can promise is that it will be worth it.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So remember these five things when life starts throwing shade your way:</span>\n\n**Where you are right now is exactly where you should be**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Being stuck in a crappy place is no fun, so much so that we will often try to avoid the reality of our situation.  We shouldn’t be here, we don’t want to be here.  But understanding that this is but one step along your path will allow you to live in the moment, happy, present and aware.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Being here now is what will get you to tomorrow.</span>\n\n**Your attitude makes all the difference**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Having a terrible attitude about your already terrible situation only compounds how terrible things really are.  Remember that you can always change your mindset or perspective on things, and doing so will help you radiate positivity.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you want a positive life, you can’t build it with a negative attitude.</span>\n\n**Each person’s path is unique to them**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you get caught up comparing your life to those of the people around you, try to ditch this habit immediately.  Comparing yourself to anyone is pointless.  Each person’s journey through this life is entirely unique to them.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The only person you should be comparing yourself to is yourself, the person you were yesterday.  </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Try to be better than that person, no one else.</span>\n\n**You must be kind to yourself**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">We’re always our own worst critic.  Sometimes what we do is never good enough for ourselves.  But speaking hurtful words about yourself does nothing to benefit you.  Try to give yourself the same leniency that you’d give your friends and family members.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You’re trying, you’re doing your best, and know that it’s enough.</span>\n\n**Practicing gratitude can only benefit you**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ungrateful people will always be able to find trouble or duress in their life, regardless of how peaceful or perfect they are.  But grateful people are able to find peace during the most troubling times.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Remember that there is always something to be grateful for, and looking for things to stay positive about during negative times shows leadership and strength.  </span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If life is a series of ups and downs like everyone says it is, sometimes life has an odd way of showing it.  I know many of us are probably wondering when the ‘ups’ are going to show up and get rid of all the downs.  Life isn’t always easy.  And no one told you it was going to be.  The only thing anyone can promise is that it will be worth it.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">So remember these five things when life starts throwing shade your way:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Where you are right now is exactly where you should be</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Being stuck in a crappy place is no fun, so much so that we will often try to avoid the reality of our situation.  We shouldn’t be here, we don’t want to be here.  But understanding that this is but one step along your path will allow you to live in the moment, happy, present and aware.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-