o be grateful for, and looking for things to stay positive about during negative times shows leadership and strength.  </span></p>	http://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2016/05/feature_image_templ2232ate.jpg	f	f	published	en_US	public	\N	\N	1	2016-05-31 06:28:28+00	1	2016-05-31 06:28:28+00	1	2016-05-31 06:28:28+00	1
1491	5c121f4e-4179-4eb9-bb3a-a3618c7d18cc	Research Finds: Marrying a Smart Woman Helps Men Live Longer	research-finds-marrying-a-smart-woman-helps-men-live-longer	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Men, when you go through the list of things you desire in a partner, does intelligence ever top your list? Attraction is of course multifaceted and complex, so all of us seek out different mates. But new research has found that intelligence might be the one thing we shouldn’t be ready to settle for, as **[brainy partners](http://www.simplemost.com/marrying-smart-woman-help-prolong-life/)**were found to extend lifespans and keep dementia at bay.</span>\n\n**[Professor Lawrence Whalley](http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3529167/Marry-intelligent-woman-defeat-dementia-men-told-Experts-say-brainy-partner-acts-buffer-disease.html)**<span style="font-weight: 400;">, emeritus professor of mental health in the College of Medicine and Life Sciences at the University of Aberdeen, had this to say during a talk entitled ‘Dementia: How Can We Protect Ourselves?’</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">“‘The thing a boy is never told he needs to do if he wants to live a longer life – but what he should do – is marry an intelligent woman. There is no better buffer (to dementia) than intelligence.”</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The study, which comes out of the **[University of Aberdeen](http://www.simplemost.com/marrying-smart-woman-help-prolong-life/)**, studied the health of identical twins and discovered that intelligent partners were a significant factor in how well a person was protected from degenerative brain diseases (like Alzheimer’s and dementia).</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It was found that men who partnered with intelligent women tended to live longer, happier lives, </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">and</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> had less risk of suffering from degenerative brain problems. This all stems from previous research showing that brain games, like **[crossword puzzles](http://iheartintelligence.com/2016/04/25/benefits-crossword-puzzles/)** for example, help stave off degenerative brain disease through stimulation of the brain.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So, it would follow that a person whose brain is engaged and stimulated by their partner regularly would gain much of the same benefit. In fact, a small number of men who were married to intelligent partners </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">did </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">show signs of dementia during brain scans, but didn’t exhibit any of the symptoms, and were actually deemed “highly intelligent” and cognitively functional.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Figuring out how to shift a cultural preference from beauty to intelligence is an endeavor we have yet to solve, however. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It has been seen that **[girls who grow up valuing their intelligence](http://everydayfeminism.com/2014/07/girls-taught-to-avoid-smart/)** tend to be more independent, as well as empowered. Young boys who value intelligence have been seen to have stronger relationships with women and show far more support for their wives and daughters.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Now, an argument can be made that choosing an intelligent wife is not only in your family’s best interest, but it is also beneficial to your overall well being and happiness!</span>\n\n \n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Men, when you go through the list of things you desire in a partner, does intelligence ever top your list? Attraction is of course multifaceted and complex, so all of us seek out different mates. But new research has found that intelligence might be the one thing we shouldn’t be ready to settle for, as <strong><a href="http://www.simplemost.com/marrying-smart-woman-help-prolong-life/">brainy partners</a></strong>were found to extend lifespans and keep dementia at bay