1410	8dec9ab5-b756-4c1d-9b14-6de753eb3117	5 Things That You Don't Need to Justify to Anyone	5-things-that-you-dont-need-to-justify-to-anyone	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the sad truths of life is that not everyone is not always going to support your decisions.  And there will certainly be times where you find yourself at a crossroads, staring down two different paths, knowing that no one can make the choice for you but yourself.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Because at the end of the day, it’s your life.  So live it how you want to live it, because the last thing you want to regret when you’ve death looming over you is that you lived a life for someone other than yourself.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five things you never need to justify to anyone else:</span>\n\n**Why you have to put yourself first**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you don’t prioritize yourself then there’s a good chance that many others will not do so either.  Investing in yourself should never been as selfish, it’s easy for many of us get caught up in putting others’ needs before our own.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Make sure that your needs and desires are being satisfied and don’t feel the need to explain why.</span>\n\n**Wanting to express your emotions**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Expressing emotion is one of the most human things a person can do.  Our emotions are there for a reason.  Never be afraid to cry, get angry or throw a fit.  It’s always better to let it out than to keep it in.  Your emotions are real.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If others judge you for doing this, they’re the ones who need an adjustment, not you.  </span>\n\n**Your weird quirky self**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">We’re all weird.  Some of us more weird than others, but we’re all weird and strange in some way.  It’s kind of weird to not be weird.  So celebrate your weirdness, it’s what makes you who you are, it’s wha