1498	68db4722-25d8-4679-8a16-d8391a283395	This is the Reason Dogs Are Always Tilting Their Heads	this-is-the-reason-dogs-are-always-tilting-their-heads	\n![](https://66.media.tumblr.com/d05d9b9f6cd069527c318f814eea2a97/tumblr_nrn1f6f66U1tq5ex7o1_400.gif)\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Okay, dogs tilting their heads at you is one of the most adorable things they can do. I’m not entirely sure why, but something about the curious look they get in their eyes and the way their ears bob back and forth a bit when they do it has me feeling all warm and fuzzy inside.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Hopefully you’ve gotten to experience it for yourself, because it’s easily one of the most heart-melting sensations a person can feel. What’s even cooler is that we now know </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">why</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> they do it.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">**[Mental Floss](http://api.viglink.com/api/click?format=go&jsonp=vglnk_147071285767412&key=d315a21d6d5a1bf22f62a7d4512f1e04&libId=irmvn3210100rbdo000DAoljp3g8ygnr3&loc=http%3A%2F%2Fhellogiggles.com%2Fdogs-tilt-heads%2F&v=1&out=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mentalfloss.com%2Farticle%2F70205%2Fwhat-makes-dogs-tilt-their-heads&title=This%20is%20why%20dogs%20tilt%20their%20heads%2C%20in%20case%20you%20were%20wondering&txt=According%20to%20Mental%20Floss)** reports that dogs like to tilt their heads as a way to empathize with their human companions (see, I told you it’s adorable). Or at least, they try to empathize with you. And this makes a lot of sense if you’ve ever owned a dog, because they somehow always pick up on our energies and are willing to lend a paw when we’re feeling down.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Tilting of the head is just another way in which they try to express their support for you; they’re trying to tell you that they’re listening to your silly human problems.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Mental Floss also notes that tilting of a dog’s head can also be an attempt to decipher where a particular noise or sound is coming from. Just as it can be hard for humans to distinguish where a sound is coming from, dog’s ears are much more sensitive and capable of hearing noises, which means they’ve got a lot more information to sort through when it comes to sound.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this case, a dog tilting its head might just be so they can figure out exactly what noise is bothering them. However, in the end, a dog’s motivation for doing most of this is simply so they can protect you in the best way possible (**[they’re that loyal](http://api.viglink.com/api/click?format=go&jsonp=vglnk_147071289063517&key=d315a21d6d5a1bf22f62a7d4512f1e04&libId=irmvnqmq0100rbdo000DA4lcf1lek&loc=http%3A%2F%2Fhellogiggles.com%2Fdogs-tilt-heads%2F2%2F%23read&v=1&out=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.the-scientist.com%2F%3Farticles.view%2FarticleNo%2F38279%2Ftitle%2FOrigin-of-Domestic-Dogs%2F&ref=http%3A%2F%2Fhellogiggles.com%2Fdogs-tilt-heads%2F&title=This%20is%20why%20dogs%20tilt%20their%20heads%2C%20in%20case%20you%20were%20wondering%20-%20Page%202%20of%202&txt=that%E2%80%99s%20a%20fact.)**). </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So, now you know! Your pup is just **[trying to relate](http://api.viglink.com/api/click?format=go&jsonp=vglnk_147071294177318&key=d315a21d6d5a1bf22f62a7d4512f1e04&libId=irmvnqmq0100rbdo000DA4lcf1lek&loc=http%3A%2F%2Fhellogiggles.com%2Fdogs-tilt-heads%2F2%2F%23read&v=1&out=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fid%2F4625213%2Fns%2Fhealth-pet_health%2Ft%2Fpuppy-love----its-better-you-think%2F&ref=http%3A%2F%2Fhellogiggles.com%2Fdogs-tilt-heads%2F&title=This%20is%20why%20dogs%20tilt%20their%20heads%2C%20in%20case%20you%20were%20wondering%20-%20Page%202%20of%202&txt=boost%20our%20mood)**to you on some level, which is something we can all understand.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><img src="https://66.media.tumblr.com/d05d9b9f6cd069527c318f814eea2a97/tumblr_nrn1f6f66U1tq5ex7o1_400.gif" alt="" /></p>\n\n<