1433	aa31fafa-bea7-420c-9ce1-211b851bc737	10 Sources of Body Pain and How They're Related to Specific Emotional States	10-sources-of-body-pain-and-how-theyre-related-to-specific-emotional-states	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Understanding what pain is will help you tremendously on your journey through life.  First and foremost, pain is energy.  Secondly, it is perception.  And lastly, pain is the physical manifestation that you feel.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Practically every bit of pain we’ve ever felt in our body is linked to various different emotional states.  These emotional states serve as warnings, indicating that we still have areas that need to be healed and subsequently grown from.  Learning our lessons and growing is the only way to rid ourselves of the pain.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain in the body is quite literal.  Certain experiences trigger certain pains, telling you what the problem is; all you need to do is figure out the lesson behind all of it.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are 10 types of body pain and their related emotional states:</span>\n\n**Muscle pains**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">These are often a result of getting ‘stuck’ on different aspects of our lives.  Whether it be at work, at home, or battles within, learning to ebb and flow with the ever changing currents of your life will ease these pains.</span>\n\n**Pain in the head**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Headaches are associated with the inability to make a decision.  And migraines, being the older brother of headaches, occur when you know what decision you need to make do not make it.  To ease these pains, remember to make time for yourself to relax and unwind each day.</span>\n\n**Neck pains**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain in the neck is linked to forgiveness, whether it be forgiving others or yourself.  Reflect on the things you love about yourself as well as the things you love about those around you; this will help you become more aware and more capable of letting go.</span>\n\n**Gum pain**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Similar to neck pain, gum pain is tied to inaction regarding decision-making.  Be assertive, be confident and make choices with purpose.</span>\n\n**Stomach pain**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain in our stomachs are related to a lack of feeling whole or fulfilled in life.  It is the result of a void within ourselves, one that leaves us in pain.</span>\n\n**Lower back pain**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Stress caused by anxiety over finances or even just a general lack of emotional support can cause pain in the lower back.  This could be a sign that it’s time you ask for a raise or work to manage your money more efficiently.</span>\n\n**Pain in the elbows**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Elbow pain is correlated with resistance to any change that may be happening in your life.  Stiffness is indicative of stiffness in your life.  You may want to consider rocking the boat a little bit; stir things up and see what happens.  All you can really do anyway is let the flow take you; be like water.</span>\n\n**Pain in the arms**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Arm pain means that you’re carrying a burden, whether it be your own or that of another person’s.  Take time to reflect on this burden and decide whether or not you need to keep carrying it.</span>\n\n**Hand pain**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Hand pain is associated with how often you’re reaching out to others.  If you’re experiencing hand pain, attempt to make new friends or reconnect with an old one.  Make plans with your coworkers or neighbors.  Build new connections.</span>\n\n**Pain in the teeth**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Teeth pains are connected to consistent negative thought patterns, ones that repeat how much you dislike your current situation.  If you practice positive thought patterns, ones that focus on how your experiences flow through you with ease, you can relieve this pain.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">h/t [**Prevent Disease**](http://preventdisease.com/news/15/060815_20-Sources-Pain-Tied-To-Specific-Emotional-States.shtml)</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Understanding what pain is will help you tremendously on your journey through life.  First and foremost, pain is energy.  Secondly, it is perception.  And lastly, pain is the physical manifestation that you feel.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Practically every bit of pain we’ve ever felt in our body is linked to various different emotional states.  These emotional states serve as warnings, indicating that we still have areas that need to be healed and subsequently grown from.  Learning our lessons and growing is the only way to rid ourselves of the pain.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain in the body is quite literal.  Certain experiences trigger certain pains, telling you what the problem is; all you need to do is figure out the lesson behind all of it.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are 10 types of body pain and their related emotional states:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Muscle pains</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">These are often a result of getting ‘stuck’ on different aspects of our lives.  Whether it be at work, at home, or battles within, learning to ebb and flow with the ever changing currents of your life will ease these pains.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Pain in the head</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Headaches are associated with the inability to make a decision.  And migraines, being the older brother of headaches, occur when you know what decision you need to make do not make it.  To ease these pains, remember to make time for yourself to relax and unwind each day.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Neck pains</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain in the neck is linked to forgiveness, whether it be forgi