1444	dce8f600-5a21-4c01-838e-ccf46041e524	5 Phrases That Are Better Than Saying 'I Love You'	5-phrases-that-are-better-than-saying-i-love-you	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’ve ever fallen in love with someone then you know that love is not the type of emotion that can be adequately conveyed with three simple words.  Love is more than lusting after physical attraction, it’s more than anything we could ever imagine.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s about loving someone for who they are, flaws and all.  It’s about being a pillar of strength during tough times.  It’s about showing how much you care in little ways.  And one of the easiest ways to express love for your person is by using your words.  Words that mean more than a simple ‘I love you.’</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five phrases that express love better than the three words we’re all used to saying so often:</span>\n\n**‘I’m lucky to be yours’**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When you’ve fallen for someone pretty hard, feeling lucky comes easy.  It happens in those moments when you’re least expecting it, when you’re suddenly overcome with an intense realization that you want this to last forever.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When you start to feel that you are unworthy of this person’s love, time, and attention, don’t forget to tell them how grateful you are to have them in your life.</span>\n\n**‘I’m sorry’**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Knowing when you’re wrong and when to apologize for your actions, words, or behaviors, is much more important than throwing out a simple ‘I love you.’  If you get caught up in a fight or make a huge mistake and know you were in the wrong, own up to it.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You don’t need to waste your time trying to prove a point if you truly care about them.  Ask for forgiveness and move forward.</span>\n\n**‘I forgive you’**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the same way that you should apologize, also be willing to forgive.  When you know that your partner is truly sorry, and their transgressions are forgivable, don’t hesitate to forgive them.  Holding grudges and staying upset is wasted energy, energy that could be spent on building and nurturing your relationship.</span>\n\n**‘I support you’**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Encouraging, motivating, and generally supporting your partner is something that they can’t get from anyone else.  It means the world when your partner has your back during times of uncertainty or change.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Never be afraid to reassure them that they’re more than capable of achieving their goals and that you’ll be by their side every step of the way.</span>\n\n**‘I’m committed to you, to us’**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Knowing that your partner is entirely faithful and committed to the love you two share is an amazing feeling.  Never hesitate to tell them that your heart is theirs or how often you think about them.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The open expression of commitment illustrates your love and sincerity for this feeling toward them.  When you’re feeling the love, tell them!</span>\n\nh/t [**ReRules**](http://www.relrules.com/9-phrases-more-important-than-i-love-you/5/)\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’ve ever fallen in love with someone then you know that love is not the type of emotion that can be adequately conveyed with three simple words.  Love is more than lusting after physical attraction, it’s more than anything we could ever imagine.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s about loving someone for who they are, flaws and all.  It’s about being a pillar of strength during tough times.  It’s about showing how much you care in little ways.  And one of the easiest ways to express love for your person is by using your words.  Words that mean more than a simple ‘I love you.’</span></p>\n\n<p><span style