1448	bc58ad75-02c9-41f9-984b-b7558cc2ec36	Shocking 100-Year-Old Secret Uncovered During Remodel of This High School	shocking-100-year-old-secret-uncovered-during-remodel-of-this-high-school	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">See the Shocking 100-Year-Old Secret Found Hiding Behind the Chalkboards of This High School</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">For daydreamers like myself, the ones who spend way too much time inside their heads pondering random notions and scenarios, we like to think about seemingly random and mundane things.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">For example, while I’m hiking through the mountains, I’ll often pretend that I’m one of the very first explorers of the territory, blazing new trails and mapping new grounds.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">And there’s no harm in picturing yourself in a life so vastly different from your own.  It’s fun and it teases your brain.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So, you can imagine how excited I was when I found this story about chalkboards that were discovered during a remodel of a high school, hanging perfectly undisturbed underneath the new ones for almost 100 years.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">While it might not make national headlines, stories like these are time machines.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">On these chalkboards, that have been hidden away from the world for decades, lie the remnants of a culture and way of living that is long gone, giving us a glimpse into what life was like in Oklahoma City in 1917.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">1917 was an interesting year.  The first jazz record was released, the Ford Model T could be seen cruising the roads, the United States would eventually find itself involved in World War I, and an Oklahoman City classroom would be given new blackboards, preserving a small moment in time. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Take a second to peruse these photos of what is now Emerson High School, as you step back in time 100 years:</span>\n\n<div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![education classroom chalkboard teaching](http://cdn9.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/0b1-600x450.jpg)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn8.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/13-600x398.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">**“I have never seen that technique in my life,” said Emerson High School Principal, Sherry Kishore, regarding this multiplication wheel.**</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn4.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/2-600x398.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">**Cursive penmanship has been largely forgotten about by a majority of schools, as the advancement of technology makes skills like typing much more practical.**</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn6.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/31-600x399.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn4.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/41-600x399.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">**Principal Kishore would end up showing the old chalkboards to her 85-year-old mother, saying that “She just stood there and cried [because] it was exactly like her classroom was when she was going to school.”**</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn4.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/61-600x798.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn9.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/52-600x798.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">**Emerson High School was built in 1895, meaning it’s seen its fair share of remodels and renovations over the years.  How these chalkboards have gone completely undetected is a mystery in itself.**</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn9.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/71-600x399.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn7.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/81-600x399.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![education chalkboard oklahoma](http://cdn9.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/111-600x401.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">**Oklahoma City and the school district are now trying to find a way to preserve these fascinating old chalkboards, so they can continue to provide a look into the past.**</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![history 1900s 20th century chalkboards Oklahoma education](http://cdn7.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/91-600x399.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass"">![education chalkboard oklahoma](http://cdn4.littlethings.com/app/uploads/2015/06/121-600x402.png)</div><div class=""GoogleActiveViewClass""></div>\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">See the Shocking 100-Year-Old Secret Found Hiding Behind the Chalkboards of This High School</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For daydreamers like myself, the ones who spend way too much time inside their heads pondering random notions and scenarios, we like to think about seemingly random and mundane things.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For example, while I’m hiking through the mountains, I’ll often pretend that I’m one of the very first explorers of the territory, blazing new trails and mapping new grounds.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">And there’s no harm in picturing yourself in a life so vastly different from your own.  It’s fun and it teases your brain.  </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">So, you can imagine how excited I was wh