1452	27834bf6-cb23-47f1-96f7-76ef85ff82ad	5 Ways to Protect Yourself from Psychic Attacks	5-ways-to-protect-yourself-from-psychic-attacks	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">For the past couple of days I’d been having these crazy bouts of insecurity, confusion and sadness, and I could not for the life of me understand why.  I’d been quite happy and carefree the week before, so why the sudden despair and feelings of uncertainty?  As it would turn out, my girlfriend had been stressing out immensely, thinking about the upcoming changes in both of our lives.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">I was unknowingly picking up on all of the energy and negativity that she was feeling, and because much of it revolved around me and our relationship, she was unknowingly directing all of that negative energy at me.  When this happens, the person being sent the energy often cannot tell the difference between their own natural thoughts and these thoughts that are being sent to them, which causes even more confusion.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Oftentimes people are unknowingly psychically attacking someone, while other times they can be doing it on purpose.  It’s important to recognize when you’re being attacked and what you can do to stop it.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are five tips for deflecting psychic attacks:</span>\n\n**Ask for help from friends, healers and mentors**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re not sure where your negative energies, thoughts and feelings are coming from, it can be helpful for your friends and family to bring you into their positive thoughts and feelings.  Don’t be afraid to ask them to think about you during their prayers, meditations and healing practices.</span>\n\n**Channel your thoughts elsewhere**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">This might take some time, but you will ultimately learn to do it.  Whenever you find yourself vulnerable, thinking negative and poisonous things about yourself, a thi