1456	866364b7-4348-40ac-86ad-78acd0ac6496	5 Common Myths About Introverts	5-common-myths-about-introverts	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Introverts catch a lot of heat from people who don’t understand their personality type. But there’s a ton of information regarding introverts all over the internet, which is a great thing because many people have introverted tendencies and don’t even know it.  You might even display some yourself.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">These five myths about introverts highlight the disconnect between how introverts are perceived and how they are in actuality:</span>\n\n**Introverts don’t like conversing with others**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It might seem like introverts rarely add to the discussion, but that’s because they don’t like to talk just to hear themselves talk.  If they can’t add anything to the conversation, then they’d prefer not to speak at all.  Bring up a subject they’re interested in, however, and prepare to listen to them talk forever.</span>\n\n**Introverts are too shy**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Introverts’ shy demeanor doesn’t come from a fear of interacting with others, they just lack any motivation to actually start interacting.  If you want to start interacting with the introvert, just begin doing it and they’ll come around eventually.</span>\n\n**Introverts are typically rude**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">An introvert’s perceived rudeness is often the result of their blunt and honest nature.  This is not how the average person operates, which means they usually find themselves struggling to fit in.  They would prefer it if everyone had the same straightforward approach to life.</span>\n\n**Introverts want to spend most of their time alone**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Yes, the introvert spends a lot of time alone, but that’s only because they enjoy their own company.  They like to work through problems and puzzles, they like to daydream about different realities.  But that doesn’t mean they never crave human connection.  In fact, they long to share their world with others.</span>\n\n**Introverts need to be fixed in order to become more extroverted**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Please, never think that introverts are flawed in some way and need fixing.  This is their natural demeanor, personality, and temperament.  They connect and interact with the world in </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">different</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> ways, not </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">worse</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> ways.  There are even studies that show introverted-ness goes up with increases in IQ.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Introverts catch a lot of heat from people who don’t understand their personality type. But there’s a ton of information regarding introverts all over the internet, which is a great thing because many people have introverted tendencies and don’t even know it.  You might even display some yourself.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">These five myths about introverts highlight the disconnect between how introverts are perceived and how they are in actuality:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Introverts don’t like conversing with others</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It might seem like introverts rarely add to the discussion, but that’s because they don’t like to talk just to hear themselves talk.  If they can’t add anything to the conversation, then they’d prefer not to speak at all.  Bring up a subject they’re interested in, however, and prepare to listen to them talk forever.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Introverts are too shy</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Introverts’ shy demeanor doesn’t come from a fear of interacting with others, they just lack any motivation to actually start interacting.  If you want to start interacting with the introvert, just begin doing it and they’ll come around eventually.</span></p