1463	0550719b-2ab8-407b-9d50-68a102c60630	6 Things To Start Doing For Yourself. #4 Is Absolutely Vital.	6-things-to-start-doing-for-yourself-4-is-absolutely-vital	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If life has you down in the dumps and you can’t seem to figure out how to get back on track, these six life tips might just do the trick.  Don’t get down on your luck; figure out what’s wrong and then work hard to fix it.  You create the reality you live in.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are six things you need to start doing for yourself right now:</span>\n\n**Spend your time with the ones who matter**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Life is too short to keep negative or toxic people in your world.  Instead, focus on the ones who you like being with, the ones who love you for who you are and who encourage your growth.  These are the people who not only love who you are, but support who you want to be.</span>\n\n**Face life’s challenges and problems head on**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Everyone has problems in their life, but our reactions and behaviors concerning them are what truly define us.  As I’m sure you know, problems don’t simply go away when they are ignored.  So, do your best right now, even if its only baby steps, to overcome the obstacles in your life.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Eventually these small steps you take every day will add up in the long run.</span>\n\n**Be brutally honest with yourself**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the biggest obstacles in finding happiness or success is being afraid to admit the reality of your situation.  Always be completely honest with yourself when it comes to what is wrong and what has to change.  At the end of the day, you are the only person you can count on.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Recognize where you are now and how you ended up here, then you can start to move toward where you want to go.</span>\n\n**Recognize that your happiness is just as important as other’s**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Many of us get so caught up in being the generous, caring individuals that we are, that we sometimes forget that we have our own needs and desires that need to be fulfilled.  Always place value on </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">you</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Remember, you can help those around you even better if you take the time to make yourself happy first.</span>\n\n**Be a genuine and proud version of yourself**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The best part about being you is that no one else in the world can do </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">you</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> as good as you do.  Don’t waste any time on trying to be like others.  Embrace every aspect of who you are; your ideas, strengths, weaknesses, flaws, talents, everything.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You know you have endless potential, so be the best version of yourself that you can be.</span>\n\n**View each mistake as a lesson to be learned**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So many people are afraid of failure.  What they do not understand is that we learn the </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">most</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> from failing.  Mistakes are fine, everyone will make plenty of them in their lifetime.  If you’re not making mistakes, you’re not truly living.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Always be open to taking risks, knowing that should you fail, you have the ability to get up, shake it off and try again.  Your mistakes are the pathway to success.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If life has you down in the dumps and you can’t seem to figure out how to get back on track, these six life tips might just do the trick.  Don’t get down on your luck; figure out what’s wrong and then work hard to fix it.  You create the reality you live in.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-we