1465	2b790d42-a5c4-4bc8-be6c-ceaddddbefd0	5 Best Plants to Grow Indoors for Air Purification	5-best-plants-to-grow-indoors-for-air-purification	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re like me and like to spend a great deal of your time being outside, surrounded by nature, you can bring a bit of that feeling into your home with the introduction of flora.  Plants in the home provide numerous benefits and they make any empty space look better.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Studies have even found that bringing fresh greenery into your abode helps **[decrease stress](http://www.aarp.org/politics-society/advocacy/info-07-2012/health-benefits-of-nature.html)**, lessen **[tension](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18329704)** and promote healing.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Place a few of these plants around your home and reap the rewards of having a bit of nature in your life.</span>\n\n**The Aloe Plant (shown above)**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Aloe is notorious for its use in relieving sunburns, stings, and cuts.  Just as it helps detox our bodies, it also helps detox the air. ** [Air pollutants](http://www.aloearborescens.org/phocadownload/aloe%20health%20efficacy.pdf)**stemming from cleaning products with chemicals are Aloe’s specialty.  </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">And, aloe acts somewhat like a pollution meter, as its leaves will show **[brown spots](http://www.aloearborescens.org/phocadownload/aloe%20health%20efficacy.pdf)** when pollution levels are high.</span>\n\n**English Ivy**\n\n![English_Ivy_(Hedera_helix)](http://ta1.universaltelegra.netdna-cdn.comhttp://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2013/12/English_Ivy_Hedera_helix.jpg)\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">**[NASA](http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/02/10/nasas-guide-to-the-best-p_n_165588.html)** released a guide for the best houseplants to grow indoors because of their filtering abilities and English Ivy topped the list.  It is believed to be the best at absorbing formaldehyde, can be hung or put on the ground, only needs moderate levels of sunlight and is incredibly easy to grow.</span>\n\n**Rubber Tree**\n\n![HK_Sheung_Wan_18_Po_Hing_Fong_barber_shop_Ficus_elastica_Indian_rubber_tree_Aug-2012](http://ta1.universaltelegra.netdna-cdn.comhttp://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2013/12/HK_Sheung_Wan_18_Po_Hing_Fong_barber_shop_Ficus_elastica_Indian_rubber_tree_Aug-2012.jpg)\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Rubber tree is a great plant to start with because it does well in dimly lit areas and cold climates.  It’s a very low maintenance plant that provides is still capable of providing all of the air purification benefits of the other plants.</span>\n\n**Snake Plant**\n\n![Snake_Plant_(Sansevieria_trifasciata_'Laurentii')](http://ta1.universaltelegra.netdna-cdn.comhttp://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2013/12/Snake_Plant_Sansevieria_trifasciata_Laurentii.jpg)\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Snake plant has the capacity to thrive with low levels of water and sunlight.  It’s incredibly efficient at absorbing carbon dioxide, and unlike other plants, it releases oxygen at night.  This makes the snake plant perfect for those wanting a better night’s rest.</span>\n\n**Peace Lily**\n\n![800px-Peace_Lily](http://ta1.universaltelegra.netdna-cdn.comhttp://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2013/12/800px-Peace_Lily.jpg)\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you prefer flowers in your home, Peace Lily might be the choice for you.  This gorgeous flower is low maintenance, does well in shaded areas and cooler temperatures, and have been seen to help reduce the amount of toxins found in the air.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re like me and like to spend a great deal of your time being outside, surrounded by nature, you can bring a bit of that feeling into your home with the introduction of flora.  Plants in the home provide numerous benefits and they make any empty space look better.</span></p>\n\n