rong>Aquarius</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Arguing is the last thing the Aquarius wants to do, so that’s what they tend to avoid, choosing to completely ignore people instead. If they can’t seem to get away from whatever it is that’s upsetting them, they’re likely to blow up just because of how frustrated they are. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Depending on who they’re arguing with, they may or may not want to continue the relationship.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Pisces</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Pisces is somewhat volatile, meaning you never know what’s going to light their fuse. If they’re having a bad day already, it’s easier for them to explode. But, they don’t enjoy confrontation and would rather avoid it. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If a smoke or a drink won’t help, they know that crying will. Of all the signs, Pisceans tend to cry the most when it comes to anger and frustration.</span></p>\n\n<p>h/t <a href="http://thespiritscience.net/2016/07/13/how-each-sign-of-the-zodiac-expresses-their-anger/"><strong>SpiritScience</strong></a></p>	http://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2016/07/feature_image_sfdgsdftemplate.jpg	f	f	published	en_US	public	\N	\N	1	2016-07-23 06:05:16+00	1	2016-07-23 06:05:16+00	1	2016-07-23 06:05:16+00	1
1478	e6d66b1d-553d-45dd-8c9e-df19dc992a95	How To Make Peace With What Is (& Make it Better!)	how-to-make-peace-with-what-is-make-it-better	\nBy [**Andrea Schulman**](https://www.facebook.com/raiseyourvibrationtoday/?fref=ts) | [**Raise Your Vibration Today **](http://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/2016/07/11/make-peace-with-what-is/)\n\n<span class="s1">The [Law of Attraction](http://www.raiseyourvibrationtoday.com "Raise Your Vibration Today") is all about paradoxes, and this is a big one: *You’ve gotta make peace with what is ****before**** you can get something better.*</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Most of us learn about the LOA and we immediately want to put it to use to make our lives better. We identify all the things we DON’T have, and we go to work to try to make them happen. </span>\n\n<span class="s1">So, we focus on the boyfriend we don’t have yet, the promotion we haven’t gotten, or the weight we haven’t lost yet.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>We focus on what is lacking in order to try to create what is wanted into our realities.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Unfortunately, this strategy doesn’t work! You’ve gotta make peace with what is first.</span>\n\n\n## <span class="s1">When life isn’t good enough as it is</span>\n\n<span class="s1">If you focused on why your life isn’t good enough as it is, you only amplify the “my life isn’t good enough” vibe. Then, thanks to the Law of Attraction, your life will continue to feel “not good enough!” Your reality will always reflect back to you your dominant belief structure.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">For example, you can’t focus on how much your hate your current home and hope you’ll be able to find one you’ll love. Sure, you may move and you may find a new home.  However, rest assured, you will be just as dissatisfied with your new home as you were with the old one. </span>\n\n<span class="s1">This is because with the LOA we are always creating whatever is a match to our dominant thought patterns.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>If we believe where we live sucks, then where we live must continue to suck. It doesn’t matter where we go or how many times we move.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">You’d be much more successful in making peace with your current home, and coming to love it as it is.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Once you make peace with your current home, you become a match to homes you love. </span><span class="s1">The universe will knock its socks off to match whatever you’re putting out there.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">So, if you want your life to be great, you have to start projecting the vibe that says “my life is great now!” This is done by making peace with what is, and loving it as it stands.</span>\n\n\n## <span class="s1">Why so many people project dissatisfaction over satisfaction</span>\n\n<span class="s1">I know making peace with what is can seem a bit counterintuitive. </span>\n\nMost people have been raised to believe they have to improve their lives, and that their lives aren’t good enough as they are. People are also often taught to evaluate the problems in their lives more closely than the blessings.\n\n<span class="s1">Unfortunately, this social programming keeps many of us stuck in a rut. This is why you know a guy who’s on his third failed marriage. This is why you have a friend who is always sick. This is why so many people go on a different diet every year.  \n</span>\n\n<span class="s1">When we focus on what’s lacking, we create more lack. On the surface things may change, but it’s just the same shit, different day.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Remind yourself of this principle of the LOA on a regular basis. When you find yourself criticizing where you are, remember you are perpetuating lack. Being happy where you stand will make you a match to people, events and situations that reinforce your happiness, not your lack.</span>\n\n\n## <span class="s1">How do you make peace with what is?</span>\n\n<span class="s1">One thing you can do right now to make peace with where you are is to play the “perspective game.” The perspective game enables you to make peace with where you are in the present moment.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">To play this game, step into someone else’s shoes and evaluate your life from an alternative perspective.  List out the things you have, and view them from the perspective of* not* having them. Imagine living a life where the things you have right now are still just dreams to you. The bigger the list, the better.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">Here is a short list of things I have in my life.  To play the perspective game, I write out the list, and then take a moment imagining my life without these blessings: </span>\n\n1. <span class="s1">I have two healthy and adorable children.</span>\n2. <span class="s1">I have a wonderful husband who loves me and treats me like a queen.</span>\n3. <span class="s1">I have a great relationship with my brother. He is a kindred spirit to me.</span>\n4. <span class="s1">I have close friends I get to spend lots of time with.</span>\n5. <span class="s1">I have a bunch of friendly and positive clients and I run my own business.</span>\n6. <span class="s1">I’m healthy and in good shape.</span>\n7. <span class="s1">I’ve had an exceptional education, and I have lots of skills and knowledge that benefit me because of it.</span>\n8. <span class="s1">I live near the beach.</span>\n9. <span class="s1">I drive my own car.</span>\n10. <span class="s1">I get to vacation several times every year.</span>\n11. <span class="s1">I own my own home.</span>\n12. <span class="s1">I have money in the bank and my expenses are always paid with ease.</span>\n13. <span class="s1">I really like all of my neighbors.</span>\n14. <span class="s1">I’ve got an awesome phone and computer and all kinds of cool technological gadgets.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">To me, each of the items on this list seems very normal to me, because they are each a part of my current reality.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>However, these things are HUGE dreams for some people out there. </span>\n\n<span class="s1">In fact, just looking at this list makes me feel like my life is pretty great.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  I can’t even imagine living a life without my relationships, my health or my education. Yet,* *there are people out there who live without these blessings every day.</span></span>\n\nIt’s very hard for me to justify dissatisfaction with my life when I look at things from this perspective.  I’m just too grateful for what I have when I look at it this way.\n\n\n## <span class="s1">Why perspective matters</span>\n\n<span class="s1">When I look at this list through the perspective of those who don’t have what I already have, it reminds me just how blessed I truly am. When I look at my life through this lens, it’s easy for me to make peace with where I am. </span>\n\n***Related Article:**[20 Heartfelt Ways to Say Thank You](http://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/2016/01/06/heartfelt-ways-to-say-thank-you/ "LOA Article")*\n\n<span class="s1">When I look through my life focused on what I *haven’t *created or achieved, it’s much, much easier to feel unfulfilled. I’m not at peace when I evaluate my life based on my unfulfilled dreams.  How at peace I am with my life has everything to do with which perspective I choose to take.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">In playing this perspective game, you come to see all of the wonderful things you have already created in your life.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>You are focused on what you HAVE rather than what you DON’T have.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>This projects a vibe that shouts out “I am fortunate in so many ways!”</span>\n\n<span class="s1">A message like this becomes reinforced in your reality, allowing more and more good things to come into your life. The universe must continue to bless you, if you believe you are blessed.</span>\n\n\n## <span class="s1">Work within the paradox!</span>\n\n<span class="s1">So, if you are wanting to use the Law of Attraction to improve your quality of life, make sure you are working within the paradox.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>You’ve gotta make peace with what is before something better will come along. </span>\n\n<span class="s1">Remember, your life is great *right here and now, regardless of where you stand.  *There are always dreams you have achieved, and there are always reasons to be grateful.* *When you acknowledge this truth and declare your life to be great, your life will reflect greatness back to you in spades.</span>\n\n<span class="s1">How is your life already great? Why is where you stand a wonderful place to be? Feel free to comment below and declare the greatness of your life right now!</span>\n\n<span class="s1">XO, Andrea</span>\n\n### Are you a student of the Law of Attraction?\n\nSign up for my free [Law of Attraction newsletter](http://raiseyourvibrationtoday.us9.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=36d05de151fc23b6dee2dd220&id=db39a47128 "subscribe") for conscious advice to help you attract positive outcomes into your life.  You can also become a member of my LOA member website and gain access to a library of video tutorials, ebooks, audiobooks and meditations.  Learn how to attract the things you want with fun, clarity and success!   Join today for as little as[ $1.99](https://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/membership-checkout/?level=1 "become a member for just $1.99!") or become an annual member for [30% in savings](https://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/membership-checkout/?level=2 "annual member").\n\n\n	\N	<p>By <a href="https://www.facebook.com/raiseyourvibrationtoday/?fref=ts"><strong>Andrea Schulman</strong></a> | <a href="http://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/2016/07/11/make-peace-with-what-is/"><em>*Raise Your Vibration Today *</em></a></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">The <a href="http://www.raiseyourvibrationtoday.com" title="Raise Your Vibration Today">Law of Attraction</a> is all about paradoxes, and this is a big one: <em>You’ve gotta make peace with what is <strong></em><em>before</em><em></strong> you can get something better.</em></span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Most of us learn about the LOA and we immediately want to put it to use to make our lives better. We identify all the things we DON’T have, and we go to work to try to make them happen. </span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">So, we focus on the boyfriend we don’t have yet, the promotion we haven’t gotten, or the weight we haven’t lost yet.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>We focus on what is lacking in order to try to create what is wanted into our realities.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Unfortunately, this strategy doesn’t work! You’ve gotta make peace with what is first.</span></p>\n\n<h2 id="spanclasss1whenlifeisntgoodenoughasitisspan"><span class="s1">When life isn’t good enough as it is</span></h2>\n\n<p><span class="s1">If you focused on why your life isn’t good enough as it is, you only amplify the “my life isn’t good enough” vibe. Then, thanks to the Law of Attraction, your life will continue to feel “not good enough!” Your reality will always reflect back to you your dominant belief structure.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">For example, you can’t focus on how much your hate your current home and hope you’ll be able to find one you’ll love. Sure, you may move and you may find a new home.  However, rest assured, you will be just as dissatisfied with your new home as you were with the old one. </span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">This is because with the LOA we are always creating whatever is a match to our dominant thought patterns.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>If we believe where we live sucks, then where we live must continue to suck. It doesn’t matter where we go or how many times we move.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">You’d be much more successful in making peace with your current home, and coming to love it as it is.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Once you make peace with your current home, you become a match to homes you love. </span><span class="s1">The universe will knock its socks off to match whatever you’re putting out there.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">So, if you want your life to be great, you have to start projecting the vibe that says “my life is great now!” This is done by making peace with what is, and loving it as it stands.</span></p>\n\n<h2 id="spanclasss1whysomanypeopleprojectdissatisfactionoversatisfactionspan"><span class="s1">Why so many people project dissatisfaction over satisfaction</span></h2>\n\n<p><span class="s1">I know making peace with what is can seem a bit counterintuitive. </span></p>\n\n<p>Most people have been raised to believe they have to improve their lives, and that their lives aren’t good enough as they are. People are also often taught to evaluate the problems in their lives more closely than the blessings.</p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Unfortunately, this social programming keeps many of us stuck in a rut. This is why you know a guy who’s on his third failed marriage. This is why you have a friend who is always sick. This is why so many people go on a different diet every year. <br />\n</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">When we focus on what’s lacking, we create more lack. On the surface things may change, but it’s just the same shit, different day.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Remind yourself of this principle of the LOA on a regular basis. When you find yourself criticizing where you are, remember you are perpetuating lack. Being happy where you stand will make you a match to people, events and situations that reinforce your happiness, not your lack.</span></p>\n\n<h2 id="spanclasss1howdoyoumakepeacewithwhatisspan"><span class="s1">How do you make peace with what is?</span></h2>\n\n<p><span class="s1">One thing you can do right now to make peace with where you are is to play the “perspective game.” The perspective game enables you to make peace with where you are in the present moment.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">To play this game, step into someone else’s shoes and evaluate your life from an alternative perspective.  List out the things you have, and view them from the perspective of* not* having them. Imagine living a life where the things you have right now are still just dreams to you. The bigger the list, the better.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Here is a short list of things I have in my life.  To play the perspective game, I write out the list, and then take a moment imagining my life without these blessings: </span></p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><span class="s1">I have two healthy and adorable children.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I have a wonderful husband who loves me and treats me like a queen.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I have a great relationship with my brother. He is a kindred spirit to me.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I have close friends I get to spend lots of time with.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I have a bunch of friendly and positive clients and I run my own business.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I’m healthy and in good shape.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I’ve had an exceptional education, and I have lots of skills and knowledge that benefit me because of it.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I live near the beach.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I drive my own car.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I get to vacation several times every year.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I own my own home.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I have money in the bank and my expenses are always paid with ease.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I really like all of my neighbors.</span>  </li>\n<li><span class="s1">I’ve got an awesome phone and computer and all kinds of cool technological gadgets.</span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span class="s1">To me, each of the items on this list seems very normal to me, because they are each a part of my current reality.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>However, these things are HUGE dreams for some people out there. </span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">In fact, just looking at this list makes me feel like my life is pretty great.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  I can’t even imagine living a life without my relationships, my health or my education. Yet,* *there are people out there who live without these blessings every day.</span></span></p>\n\n<p>It’s very hard for me to justify dissatisfaction with my life when I look at things from this perspective.  I’m just too grateful for what I have when I look at it this way.</p>\n\n<h2 id="spanclasss1whyperspectivemattersspan"><span class="s1">Why perspective matters</span></h2>\n\n<p><span class="s1">When I look at this list through the perspective of those who don’t have what I already have, it reminds me just how blessed I truly am. When I look at my life through this lens, it’s easy for me to make peace with where I am. </span></p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Related Article:</strong><a href="http://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/2016/01/06/heartfelt-ways-to-say-thank-you/" title="LOA Article">20 Heartfelt Ways to Say Thank You</a></em></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">When I look through my life focused on what I *haven’t *created or achieved, it’s much, much easier to feel unfulfilled. I’m not at peace when I evaluate my life based on my unfulfilled dreams.  How at peace I am with my life has everything to do with which perspective I choose to take.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">In playing this perspective game, you come to see all of the wonderful things you have already created in your life.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>You are focused on what you HAVE rather than what you DON’T have.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>This projects a vibe that shouts out “I am fortunate in so many ways!”</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">A message like this becomes reinforced in your reality, allowing more and more good things to come into your life. The universe must continue to bless you, if you believe you are blessed.</span></p>\n\n<h2 id="spanclasss1workwithintheparadoxspan"><span class="s1">Work within the paradox!</span></h2>\n\n<p><span class="s1">So, if you are wanting to use the Law of Attraction to improve your quality of life, make sure you are working within the paradox.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>You’ve gotta make peace with what is before something better will come along. </span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">Remember, your life is great <em>right here and now, regardless of where you stand.  *There are always dreams you have achieved, and there are always reasons to be grateful.</em> *When you acknowledge this truth and declare your life to be great, your life will reflect greatness back to you in spades.</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">How is your life already great? Why is where you stand a wonderful place to be? Feel free to comment below and declare the greatness of your life right now!</span></p>\n\n<p><span class="s1">XO, Andrea</span></p>\n\n<h3 id="areyouastudentofthelawofattraction">Are you a student of the Law of Attraction?</h3>\n\n<p>Sign up for my free <a href="http://raiseyourvibrationtoday.us9.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=36d05de151fc23b6dee2dd220&amp;id=db39a47128" title="subscribe">Law of Attraction newsletter</a> for conscious advice to help you attract positive outcomes into your life.  You can also become a member of my LOA member website and gain access to a library of video tutorials, ebooks, audiobooks and meditations.  Learn how to attract the things you want with fun, clarity and success!   Join today for as little as<a href="https://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/membership-checkout/?level=1" title="become a member for just $1.99!"> $1.99</a> or become an annual member for <a href="https://raiseyourvibrationtoday.com/membership-checkout/?level=2" title="annual member">30% in 