1483	83463417-9a2a-426f-be14-b074e36fde1e	You’re Less Likely to Find Love if You’re Intelligent and Independent, Here's Why:	youre-less-likely-to-find-love-if-youre-intelligent-and-independent-heres-why	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Have you ever thought about how love changes and grows to mean different things at different points in your life? The love you were looking for in your teenage years is not the same love that you were looking for in your twenties, a trend that I would imagine continues to hold up as we all grow older.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">But an interesting thing happens as we mature into old age. Love starts to become more delicate, more complicated. Not only does it become harder to fall in love, but truly letting go of any painful past loves can be even harder.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You would think that it would get easier as we move through the motions of each relationship or romantic experience, but it’s actually our deep understanding of relationships that makes the whole process so much more difficult.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Just as with most things in life, our perceptions create the emotions that we feel. Love is not inherently magical; it is our feelings and perceptions that create this feeling of magic. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Unfortunately, as we get older, that magic starts to wane, simply because our understanding of relationships (and our roles within them) becomes so clear that there’s no room left for mystery or magic.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">So, is there anyway to combat this? Kind of. One of the only ways we fall in love as we grow older is feeling that we </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">need</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> love. If you’re of the mindset that you don’t deserve love or truly need it, then it will never come your way.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">I found love when I decided that I was ready to