1484	8a4609ef-b838-49b6-ad55-17cfd890e5a1	The People of India Just Planted 50 Million New Trees in 24 Hours	the-people-of-india-just-planted-50-million-new-trees-in-24-hours	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Recently, the country of India saw over 800,000 volunteers flood the streets of Uttar Pradesh state, planting 50 million new trees in just 24 hours as they attempted to set a new world record. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">As a country that serves as home to [six of the top ten cities](http://www.sciencealert.com/these-are-the-10-cities-with-the-worst-air-pollution-in-the-world) with the worst quality of air in the world, India’s latest efforts illustrate their continued commitment to reducing the effects of climate change.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Other projects that India has championed include having the world’s first [completely solar powered airport](http://www.sciencealert.com/india-establishes-world-s-first-100-percent-solar-powered-airport) and the world’s biggest [solar power station](http://www.sciencealert.com/world-s-largest-solar-power-station-planned-for-india). Furthermore, solar energy is now [cheaper than coal](http://www.sciencealert.com/india-says-the-cost-of-solar-power-is-now-cheaper-than-coal) in the country.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The record that they’re hoping to beat was set by Pakistan back in 2013 when they planted 847,275 trees. As we speak, Guinness World Record auditors are working on counting through the high number of trees planted by India’s close to 800,000 volunteers. But due to the high number of volunteers, it is expected that they will achieve their goal.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">“The biggest contribution of this tree planting project is, apart from the tokenism, that it focuses on the major issues,” </span>[<span style="font-weight: 400;">said Anit Mukherjee</span>](http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/15/india-plants-50-million-trees-in-24-hours/)<span st