1485	6ac53021-4911-4ffa-a585-0b3cd258c8f9	What Addictions Are You Most Likely to Have, Based on Your Zodiac Sign	what-addictions-are-you-most-likely-to-have-based-on-your-zodiac-sign	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Addiction takes hold in almost everyone’s life, regardless of who we are, because addiction is unique for everyone. Maybe you’re addicted to playing video games, maybe you’re addicted to working out, or maybe you’ve dabbled with addiction to hard drugs; either way, each and every addiction is indicative of a bigger problem in a person’s life.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">And each zodiac sign is complete with its own set of problems that we have to deal with.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Addiction can be a very detrimental aspect of life if it is not recognized until it’s too late, so here is a bit of insight as to what each sign is most likely to gravitate toward:</span>\n\n**Aries **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(March 21 – April 19) | Cocaine</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">As one of the youngest signs of the zodiac, Aries are often of the opinion that life doesn’t move quick enough. Their personalities are usually a big mess of confidence mixed together with neediness.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">They’re likely to choose cocaine over other substances because it reinforces their already fantastical perspective that they’re always slightly ahead of everyone else.</span>\n\n**Taurus **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(April 20 – May 20) | Cannabis / Food / Both</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Taurus have almost too much patience for their own good. This patience oftentimes transforms into laziness, which means that the Taurus isn’t going to go out of his or her way to develop an addiction to crack or meth, simply because it’s a lot harder to find.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Food is the most likely addiction; pick up the phone, punch in some numbers, and food is at your door within 20 minutes.</span>\n\n**Gemini **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(May 21 – June 20) | Social Media</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Certain studies have found that Facebook can be more addictive than alcohol, a notion that Gemini can easily understand. Gemini hide from their feelings by compulsively communicating, jumping from conversation to the next.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">They tend to enjoy doing a variety of different things, but never really get too involved with any of them. </span>\n\n**Cancer **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(June 21 – July 22) | Heroin</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Heroin suits the Cancer almost perfectly, as they prefer to retreat into reclusivity when the world around them starts to crumble. Wherever they gain the most comfort and security is where the Cancer gravitates to, and heroin has oft been described as being taken to a world literally everything is </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">okay</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">, as if you were a baby again without a care in the world.</span>\n\n**Leo **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(July 23 – August 22) | Shopping</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Leos tend to have materialistic tendencies, and vanity is one of their hallmark characteristics, so it makes perfect sense that a Leo would struggle with finances and irresponsible spending. Leo women like to sport designer clothing and expensive jewelry, while Leo men prefer to spend their money on new gadgets and luxury vehicles.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">This all plays on the bigger issue of the Leo’s innate desire to be in the limelight as much as possible.</span>\n\n**Virgo **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(August 23 – September 22) | Codependency</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Virgo people naturally gravitate toward being in positions of caretaking, often putting their unique ability to problem solve and care for others to good use on those they care about. The downside to this trait becomes obvious when they put </span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;">too much</span>*<span style="font-weight: 400;"> focus on the well being of others, and not enough on their own.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Virgos sometimes unconsciously seek out people who are struggling in life, seemingly unable to care for themselves. This lets them put their own life problems on the backburner in order to fix someone else’s.</span>\n\n**Libra **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(September 23 – October 22) | Love</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ironically, as a sign that represents fairness and balance, Libras often struggle to embody the values that their sign is known for. From the start, they expect life to operate on a level of fairness that simply doesn’t exist, which frustrates them to the point of tears.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To add to the fire, they have a constant need for a partner to make them feel balanced. The Libra should focus on finding balance in their own life by getting rid of ridiculous expectations, and by not treating relationships like they’re the end-all-be-all.</span>\n\n**Scorpio **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(October 23 – November 21) | Sex / Porn</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Scorpios are notorious for their adventurous nature in the bedroom; they’re highly passionate beings who consider sex to be very important in a relationship. Tie this in with their secluded and voyeuristic nature, and porn becomes a preferred sexual outlet.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Complex and somewhat confusing, while Scorpios truly desire intimate connection and passion with others, it’s also something that scares them the most.</span>\n\n**Sagittarius **<span style="font-weight: 400;">(November 22 – December 21) | Gambling / Drinking</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sagittarius is a sign closely tied to Jupiter, the planet of luck and gifts. They have a 