1486	415905fa-7f4f-4af6-a9a6-cb22be731a05	5 Signs You're an Introvert, and Not Just Shy	5-signs-youre-an-introvert-and-not-just-shy	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">While introverts and shy people exhibit a lot of the same behaviors, the two personality types are worlds away from each other. Many people who are actually introverts often get described as ‘shy’ by their friends and family, but that’s simply because they don’t know the difference. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Shyness is a trait that stems from a person’s fears and insecurities. Introverted folks don’t have a fear of people, it’s simply that being social is an exhausting endeavor for them. They need time alone to rejuvenate their energy and aren’t keen on talking just to talk.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you feel shy, but unafraid, you might just be an introvert. Here are five easy ways to tell:</span>\n\n**Small talk isn’t your thing**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Introverts tend to be thinkers and intellectuals, so they’re not super enthused about conversations that lack real substance. If you want to talk about big ideas, like life, ideology, theories, goals, etc., the introvert will undoubtedly open up. They’re good at listening and are good at picking up on subtle social cues.</span>\n\n**You take your time to respond to texts or messages**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you like to take the time to develop a thoughtful reply to the texts and messages you receive, you might be introverted. They don’t like to fire off random thoughts and ideas without feeling fully invested in what’s being said, just as they’re likely to stay quiet in a social setting if they feel they have nothing important to add to the conversation.</span>\n\n**Crowds and groups of people overwhelm you**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Being around numerous people in close proximity to one another can be overstimulating for the introvert. They would much rather spend time with a few close friends, but even then, they’ll need alone time at some point to recharge. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you find yourself feeling drained after being social for prolonged periods of time, you’re definitely introverted.</span>\n\n**Anti-social? No, *****selectively social***\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Introverted people can sometimes struggle to find people they’re entirely comfortable being around. And they’re not about to invest a ton of time and energy into a person that they’re not 100 percent on board with. If you like to take the time to get to know someone before getting personal with them, you’re probably introverted. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your social circle might be small, but all of your relationships are somewhat special.</span>\n\n**You’re a deeply loyal friend**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Loyalty often tops the list of an introvert’s valuable traits. They’re highly selective nature when it comes to relationships means that they’re fully committed to the people they choose to be around. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Their inner circle is a wonderful place to be, because once you’ve made it, there’s a good chance you’ve gained a lifelong loyal friend.</span>\n\nh/t [**Life Hack**](http://www.lifehack.org/285869/24-signs-youre-introvert-not-shy)\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">While introverts and shy people exhibit a lot of the same behaviors, the two personality types are worlds away from each other. Many people who are actually introverts often get described as ‘shy’ by their friends and family, but that’s simply because they don’t know the difference. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shyness is a trait that stems from a person’s fears and insecurities. Introverted folks don’t have a fear of people, it’s simply that being social is an exhausting endeavor for them. They need time alone to rejuvenate their energy and aren’t keen on talking just to talk.</