ight</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain lasting anywhere from 2 hours to 72 hours</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Numbness</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Tingling</span>\n\n**Why are you getting migraines in the first place?**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Migraines happen for a lot of different reasons, so it’s not always obvious why you’re suffering from one. While we can’t say for certain why each individual migraine occurs, there is a list of known causes you can study in order to take preventative measures:</span>\n\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">[Stress is one reason](http://www.webmd.com/migraines-headaches/guide/migraines-headaches-managing-stress). Chronic stress can cause headaches that eventually turn into the nightmares that are migraines.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">The [consumption of alcohol](http://www.joybauer.com/photo-gallery/common-trigger-foods/alcohol/) has been linked to people’s development of migraines.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Allergies have been seen to set off certain reactions that can cause migraines.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">Any sort of vitamin or mineral deficiency can start migraines.</span>\n- <span style="font-weight: 400;">The most common circumstances linked to migraines are [dehydration](http://www.webmd.com/a-to-z-guides/dehydration-adults) and an [imbalance of electrolytes](http://www.healthline.com/health/electrolyte-disorders). Not only will you feel incredibly sluggish or lethargic, but these conditions create the perfect environment for brewing headaches.</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Migraine headaches cause some of the most agonizing pain humans have ever felt. The worst ones can leave you bedridden or completely incapacitated. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you or a loved one suffer from migraines, we have some good news for you: lemon juice and salt water will clear them right up, and in 