1494	6afa98b4-5c8f-4773-ac85-d91e10fa807a	4 Reasons That Long Distance BFFs Make the Best BFFs	4-reasons-that-long-distance-bffs-make-the-best-bffs	\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you have a BFF, you’re pretty lucky. Not everyone is blessed with loving friends, let alone one good, amazing friend who always has your back no matter what. I recently stumbled across a BFF of my own and I have to say, it’s a pretty great feeling. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Maybe you have a BFF, but he or she lives across the world from you, making your relationship more long distance than anything. But that’s not necessarily a bad thing! </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Some of the closest and most passionate relationships happen at a distance, so if you have a long distance BFF, here are four reasons that they’re so great:</span>\n\n**You don’t have any other choice but to communicate with one another**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Because your long distance BFF might not run into you at the store, make a surprise visit to your place of work for some lunch, or get to meet up with you for happy hour on Friday, you have to actually work to communicate with them.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">This means you set aside time specifically for them to discuss the important happenings of life. Whether it’s a big promotion at work or a crazy story from the weekend, your communication is valued and genuine.</span>\n\n**They help you see from other perspectives**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s incredibly easy to get so caught up in your own life that you forget there’s an entire world that exists outside of your own. Your long distance BFF, who is outside of it all, knows exactly how to bring you back to a grounded state: they’ll tell you how it is, no sugarcoating. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">As someone who only has your best interests in mind, the long distance BFF will always give you real advice when you need it. You don’t need to worry about them having ulterior motives or wanting to stir up drama, because they’re a thousand miles away.</span>\n\n**The time you do get to spend together is priceless**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">‘Reunited and it feels so good’ has never been more accurate than when two long distance BFFs come together after a long time apart. This is definitely one case where absence makes the heart grow fonder. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Even if the two of you talk on the phone regularly, you never run out of things to say and share when you finally meet up in person.</span>\n\n**Your relationship takes work from both of you, work you can be proud of**\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Every person who’s ever had a BFF knows that it’s not always sunshine and rainbows. Having good friends isn’t always easy, but it’s almost always worth it. Having that BFF be long distance only adds to the work. You have to want it in order for it work. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re content sending a text every now and then when you remember something funny or simply don’t have time to communicate, you’re not showing the other person that you want them in your life.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Good friends are hard to come by, so if you and your friend put in the time and effort to make it work, that’s something you can both be proud of. So, take the time to let your long distance BFF know just how important they are to you!</span>\n\n\n	\N	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you have a BFF, you’re pretty lucky. Not everyone is blessed with loving friends, let alone one good, amazing friend who always has your back no matter what. I recently stumbled across a BFF of my own and I have to say, it’s a pretty great feeling. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Maybe you have a BFF, but he or she lives across the world from you, making your relationship more long distance than anything. But that’s not necessarily a bad thing! </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Some of the closest and most passionate relationships happen at a distance, so if you have a long distance BFF, here are four reasons that they’re so great:</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>You don’t have any other choice but to communicate with one another</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Because your long distance BFF might not run into you at the store, make a surprise visit to your place of work for some lunch, or get to meet up with you for happy hour on Friday, you have to actually work to communicate with them.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This means you set aside time specifically for them to discuss the important happenings of life. Whether it’s a big promotion at work or a crazy story from the weekend, your communication is valued and genuine.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>They help you see from other perspectives</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s incredibly easy to get so caught up in your own life that you forget there’s an entire world that exists outside of your own. Your long distance BFF, who is outside of it all, knows exactly how to bring you back to a grounded state: they’ll tell you how it is, no sugarcoating. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">As someone who only has your best interests in mind, the long distance BFF will always give you real advice when you need it. You don’t need to worry about them having ulterior motives or wanting to stir up drama, because they’re a thousand miles away.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>The time you do get to spend together is priceless</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">‘Reunited and it feels so good’ has never been more accurate than when two long distance BFFs come together after a long time apart. This is definitely one case where absence makes the heart grow fonder. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Even if the two of you talk on the phone regularly, you never run out of things to say and share when you finally meet up in person.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Your relationship takes work from both of you, work you can be proud of</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Every person who’s ever had a BFF knows that it’s not always sunshine and rainbows. Having good friends isn’t always easy, but it’s almost always worth it. Having that BFF be long distance only adds to the work. You have to want it in order for it work. </span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re content sending a text every now and then when you remember something funny or simply don’t have time to communicate, you’re not showing the other person that you want them in your life.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Good friends are hard to come by, so if you and your friend put in the time and effort to make it work, that’s something you can both be proud of. So, take the time to let your long distance BFF know just how important they are to you!</span></p>	http://cdn.heartcenteredrebalancing.com/2016/08/feature_image_temp65656late.jpg	f	f	published	en_US	public	\N	\N	1	2016-08-09 08:02:58+00	1	2016-08-09 08:02:58+00	1	2016-08-09 08:02:58+00	1
